<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusse v&otilde;tmise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for Employment in Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikule esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for state or local government officials </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikuna v&otilde;ib teenistusse v&otilde;tta 18-aastaseks saanud v&auml;hemalt keskharidusega teov&otilde;imelise Eesti kodaniku, kes valdab eesti keelt seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel s&auml;testatud ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An Estonian citizen who has attained eighteen years of age, has at least a secondary education, has active legal capacity and is proficient in Estonian to the extent provided by or pursuant to law may be employed in the service as a state or local government official. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&otilde;rgema v&otilde;i vanemametniku ametikohale v&otilde;ib riigiteenistuses nimetada 21-aastaseks saanud ja v&auml;hemalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udmistele vastava isiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who has attained 21 years of age and complies at least with the requirements provided for in subsection (1) of this Act may be appointed to a position of higher or senior official in the state public service. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. (Kehtetu - 20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. (Repealed - 20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikud, keda ei v&otilde;i v&otilde;tta teenistusse </eesti>
<inglise>Persons who shall not be employed in service </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusse ei v&otilde;i v&otilde;tta isikut: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall not be employed in the service: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kellel on karistatus tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person under punishment for an intentionally committed criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kes on eeluurimise v&otilde;i kohtu all s&uuml;&uuml;distatuna kuriteos, mille eest seadus n&auml;eb ette vabadusekaotuse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person under preliminary investigation for or a person accused of a criminal offence for which the law prescribes imprisonment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kellelt on j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsusega &auml;ra v&otilde;etud teataval ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tamise v&otilde;i teataval tegevusalal tegutsemise &otilde;igus - niisugusele ametikohale v&otilde;i tegevusalale; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person deprived of the right to work in a particular position or to operate in a particular area of activity by a court judgment which has entered into force, in such office or area of activity; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kes on l&auml;hisuguluses (vanavanemad, vanemad, vennad, &otilde;ed, lapsed, lapselapsed) v&otilde;i h&otilde;imluses (abikaasa, abikaasa vanemad, vennad, &otilde;ed, lapsed) vastavat ametikohta vahetult kontrolliva ametniku v&otilde;i vahetu &uuml;lemusega." ; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons who are in a close relationship (grandparents, parents, brothers, sisters, children, grandchildren) or in a close relationship by marriage (spouse, spouse's parents, brothers, sisters, children) with an official or the immediate superior who has direct control over the corresponding position; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>5) keda on karistatud haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalkorras korruptiivse teo eest. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a person who has been punished for an act of corruption under administrative or criminal procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusse v&otilde;tmise teistsuguste v&otilde;i t&auml;iendavate n&otilde;uete kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of different or supplementary requirements for employment in service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusse v&otilde;tmise teistsugused n&otilde;uded kehtestatakse seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Different requirements for employment in the service shall be established by law or pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistusse v&otilde;tmise t&auml;iendavad n&otilde;uded kehtestatakse seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Supplementary requirements for employment in the service shall be established by or pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendavaid kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;udeid v&otilde;ib kehtestada ametiasutuse juht v&otilde;i temast k&otilde;rgemalseisev &uuml;lemus v&otilde;i ametiasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of an administrative agency, or a person or administrative agency superior to him or her may establish supplementary qualification requirements. </inglise>
