<eesti>Ametniku teenistusse v&otilde;tmise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Employment of Official in Service </inglise>
<eesti>1. jaotis. </eesti>
<inglise>Subdivision 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &uuml;ldkord </eesti>
<inglise>General procedure for employment of official in service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnikud, kellele ei laiene k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvid 19 - 36 </eesti>
<inglise>Officials to whom &sect;&sect; 19 - 36 of this Act shall not extend </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvid 19 - 36 ei laiene Riigikogu ja kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu poolt ametisse nimetatavatele ja valitavatele isikutele ning Vabariigi Presidendi poolt ametisse nimetatavatele isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>Sections 19 - 36 of this Act shall not extend to persons elected or appointed to office by the Riigikogu or a local government council, or to persons appointed to office by the President of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistusse v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Employment of official in service </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik v&otilde;etakse teenistusse ametisse nimetamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>An official shall be employed in the service by appointment to office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igus on ametiasutuse juhil v&otilde;i tema poolt selleks volitatud ametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of an administrative agency or an official authorised by him or her has appointment authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnikud, kelle nimetamise &otilde;igus on ametiasutusel v&otilde;i k&otilde;rgemalseisval &uuml;lemusel, s&auml;testatakse seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Officials the appointment authority of whom rests with an administrative agency or a superior person shall be provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistust&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term of service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik v&otilde;etakse teenistusse ametiasutuse koosseisus etten&auml;htud vabale ametikohale m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be employed in the service in a vacant position on the staff of an administrative agency for an unspecified period of time, except in the cases provided for in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks v&otilde;etakse teenistusse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall be employed in the service for a specified period of time: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku asendaja - asendatava ametikohale naasmiseni v&otilde;i ametist vabastamiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a substitute for a temporarily absent official, until the return to or release from office of the person substituted; </inglise>
<eesti>2) konkursi korras ametisse nimetatava ametniku kohuset&auml;itja - konkursikomisjoni otsuses m&auml;rgitud isiku ametisse astumiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an acting official in a position to be filled by way of competition, until the assumption of office by the person designated in the decision of a competition committee; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Riigikogu esimehe v&otilde;i aseesimehe n&otilde;unik ja abi, Riigikogu fraktsiooni v&otilde;i ajutise komisjoni n&otilde;unik ja konsultant - Riigikogu antud koosseisu volituste ajaks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui Riigikogu esimehe v&otilde;i aseesimehe volituste l&otilde;puni v&otilde;i Riigikogu fraktsiooni v&otilde;i ajutise komisjoni tegevuse l&otilde;ppemiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>3) an adviser or assistant to the President or Vice-President of the Riigikogu, an adviser or consultant to a faction or temporary committee of the Riigikogu, for the term of office of a given membership of the Riigikogu, but for not longer than the expiry of the term of office of the President or Vice-President of the Riigikogu, or the termination of activities of the faction or temporary committee of the Riigikogu; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Vabariigi Presidendi n&otilde;unik - Vabariigi Presidendi volituste ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) an adviser to the President of the Republic, for the term of office of the President of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>5) peaministri v&otilde;i ministri n&otilde;unik ja abi - vastavalt Vabariigi Valitsuse v&otilde;i ministri volituste ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) an adviser or assistant to the Prime Minister or a minister, for the term of office of the Government of the Republic or the minister, respectively; </inglise>
<eesti>5 (1)) ministeeriumi kantsler - viieks aastaks; </eesti>
<inglise>5 (1)) a secretary general of a ministry, for five years; </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>6) koosseisuv&auml;line ametnik - &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmise ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a non-staff official, for the time needed for the performance of a function. </inglise>
<eesti>7) riiklik lepitaja - kollektiivse t&ouml;&ouml;t&uuml;li lahendamise seaduses (RT I 1993, 26, 442; 1996, 3, 57; 1998, 57, 858) etten&auml;htud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>7) a Public Conciliator, for the term prescribed in the Collective Labour Dispute Resolution Act (RT I 1993, 26, 442; 1996, 3, 57; 1998, 57, 858). </inglise>
<eesti>(02.06.98 j&otilde;ust.06.07.98 - RT I 1998, 57, 858) </eesti>
<inglise>(02.06.98 entered into force 06.07.98 - RT I 1998, 57, 858) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku vabastamisel ametikohalt, v&auml;lja arvatud Riigikogu esimehe v&otilde;i aseesimehe v&otilde;i peaministri v&otilde;i ministri n&otilde;uniku v&otilde;i abi v&otilde;i Riigikogu fraktsiooni v&otilde;i ajutise komisjoni n&otilde;uniku v&otilde;i konsultandi v&otilde;i Vabariigi Presidendi n&otilde;uniku kohalt, tehakse asendajale ettepanek asuda vabanenud ametikohale m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks teenistusse v&otilde;etud ametnikuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the release of a temporarily absent official from office, except from the office of adviser or assistant to the President or Vice-President of the Riigikogu, or to the Prime Minister or a minister, of adviser or consultant to a faction or temporary committee of the Riigikogu, or of adviser to the President of the Republic, a proposal shall be made to the substitute to fill the vacant position as an official employed for an unspecified period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku vabastamisel konkursi korras t&auml;idetavalt ametikohalt tehakse tema asendajale ettepanek asuda vabanenud ametikohale konkursi korras ametisse nimetatava ametniku kohuset&auml;itjana. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the release of a temporarily absent official from an office filled by way of competition, a proposal shall be made to his or her substitute to fill the vacant position as an acting official in an office to be filled by way of competition. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku katseaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Probationary period for official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igust omav isik v&otilde;ib, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel, kohaldada ametniku ametisse nimetamisel katseaega kestusega mitte &uuml;le kuue kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person with employment authority may, except in the cases provided for in subsection (3) of this section, apply a probationary period of not longer than six months upon the appointment of an official to office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Katseajal hinnatakse ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;tulemusi ja vastavust ametikohal esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During a probationary period, the work results and whether the official meets the requirements set for his or her position shall be assessed. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne katseaja l&otilde;ppu viib vahetu &uuml;lemus ametnikuga l&auml;bi vestluse, mille tulemused kantakse ametniku atesteerimislehele. </eesti>
<inglise>Prior to the end of the probationary period, the immediate superior shall conduct an interview with the official, the results of which shall be entered in the evaluation record of the official. </inglise>
<eesti>Ebarahuldavate tulemuste korral v&otilde;ib ametniku katseaja kestel vabastada k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 117 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 1 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of unsatisfactory results, the official may be released during the probationary period pursuant to clause 117 (1) 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Katseaega ei kohaldata: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A probationary period shall not apply: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametnikule, kelle nimetab ametisse Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i peaminister; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to an official appointed to office by the Government of the Republic or by the Prime Minister; </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametikoha t&auml;itmisel edutamise korras; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if a position is filled by way of promotion; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku asendajale v&otilde;i kohuset&auml;itjale vabale ametikohale nimetamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) upon the appointment to a vacant position of a substitute or acting official for a temporarily absent official. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Katseaja hulka ei arvata aega, mil teenistussuhe oli peatatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punktide 1-4 ja 6 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The time during which a service relationship is suspended pursuant to clauses 108 1) -4) and 6) of this Act is not included in probationary period. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusse astumiseks esitatavad dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents submitted for entry into service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kes soovib teenistusse astuda, esitab isikule, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who desires entry into the service shall submit to a person authorised to employ him or her in the service: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kirjaliku avalduse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application in writing; </inglise>
<eesti>2) elulookirjelduse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a curriculum vitae; </inglise>
<eesti>3) omak&auml;elise kinnituse, et ta vastab teenistusse astumiseks seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a confirmation under the hand of the applicant that he or she meets the requirements of the service provided by law; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tunnistuse (diplomi) vajaliku kvalifikatsiooni v&otilde;i hariduse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a certificate (diploma) regarding the necessary qualification or education; </inglise>
<eesti>5) isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi; </eesti>
<inglise>5) identification; </inglise>
<eesti>6) talle v&auml;ljaantud t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the employment record book issued to him or her; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muud seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel n&otilde;utavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>7) other documents required by or pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik, kes soovib teenistusse astuda, v&otilde;ib avaldusele lisada ka muid dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who desires entry into the service may also append other documents to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse nimetamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of appointment to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametisse nimetamine vormistatakse k&auml;skkirja v&otilde;i korraldusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An appointment to office shall be made by way of a directive or order. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;skkiri v&otilde;i korraldus peab vastama haldusdokumentidele esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele ja sisaldama v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The directive or order must comply with the requirements set for administrative documents and shall contain at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametisse nimetatava isiku ees- ja perekonnanime; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name and surname of the person appointed to office; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ametiasutuse nimetust, kuhu isik teenistusse v&otilde;etakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name of the administrative agency in which the person is employed; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametikoha nimetust ning palgaastet, palgam&auml;&auml;ra ja lisatasusid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the title of position and salary grade, salary rate and additional remuneration; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ametisse astumiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud kuup&auml;eva; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the date specified for assumption of office; </inglise>
<eesti>5) m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks ametisse nimetamisel - teenistust&auml;htaega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) in the case of appointment to office for a specified period of time, the term of service; </inglise>
<eesti>6) katseaja kohaldamisel - katseaja kestust; </eesti>
<inglise>6) in the case of a probationary period, the term of the probationary period; </inglise>
<eesti>7) avaliku teenistuse staa&zcaron;i pikkust v&otilde;i puudumist ametisse nimetamise kuup&auml;eva seisuga. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the length or absence of public service as at the date of appointment to office. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Auml;rakiri ametisse nimetamise k&auml;skkirjast v&otilde;i korraldusest antakse ametisse nimetatud isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A copy of the directive or order regarding appointment to office shall be given to the person appointed to office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuse algus ja selle edasil&uuml;kkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Commencement of service and postponement thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik on teenistuses ametisse astumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official is in the service as of the date of assumption of office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametisse astumine l&uuml;kkub kuni seitsmeks kalendrip&auml;evaks edasi, kui ametisse astumist takistavaks p&otilde;hjuseks on isiku haigus v&otilde;i vigastus v&otilde;i ootamatult tekkinud isiklikku v&otilde;i perekondlikku laadi takistus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Assumption of office shall be postponed for up to seven calendar days if the assumption of office is prevented by reason of illness or injury of the person, or an unexpected personal or family related matter. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse astumise edasil&uuml;kkamise &uuml;le seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva otsustab isik, kellel on teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>Postponement of assumption of office beyond seven calendar days shall be decided by a person with employment authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isik, kellel on teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus, v&otilde;ib ametisse nimetatud isiku taotlusel ametisse astumist edasi l&uuml;kata ka p&otilde;hjusel, mida ei ole k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person with employment authority may, at the request of a person appointed to office, also postpone the assumption of office for a reason not specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse nimetamise t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of appointment to office </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omav isik t&uuml;histab ametisse nimetamise k&auml;skkirja v&otilde;i korralduse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>A person with appointment authority shall repeal a directive or order regarding appointment to office if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametisse nimetatud isik esitab enne ametisse astumiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud kuup&auml;eva sellekohase avalduse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person appointed to office submits a petition to this effect before the date specified for assumption of office; </inglise>
<eesti>2) enne ametisse astumist ilmnevad seaduses s&auml;testatud asjaolud, mis v&auml;listavad ametisse nimetamise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) circumstances, provided by law, which preclude the appointment to office become known before assumption of office; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isik ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks ametisse astunud, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui ametisse astumine l&uuml;kkus edasi k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 25 2. v&otilde;i 3. l&otilde;ike alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person appointed to office has not assumed office by the specified time, except if the assumption of office was postponed pursuant to subsections 25 (2) or (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) isik keeldub ametivande andmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person refuses to take an oath of office. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametisse nimetamise t&uuml;histamisega kaasnev kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation arising from cancellation of appointment to office </inglise>
<eesti>Isik, kelle ametisse nimetamine t&uuml;histatakse, on kohustatud tagastama kogu ametisse nimetamise t&otilde;ttu saadu. </eesti>
<inglise>A person whose appointment to office is cancelled is required to return everything received due to the appointment to office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametivanne </eesti>
<inglise>Oath of office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik annab esmakordsel ametisse astumisel teda ametisse nimetanud isikule kirjaliku ametivande: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon assumption of office for the first time, an official shall take, before the person who has appointed him or her, the following oath of office in writing: </inglise>
<eesti>"T&otilde;otan olla ustav Eesti p&otilde;hiseaduslikule korrale ning kohusetundlikult ja t&auml;pselt t&auml;ita &uuml;lesandeid, milleks usaldatud amet mind kohustab.Tean, et avaliku teenistuse eetikakoodeksi ja teenistuskohustuste rikkumise eest on seadus kehtestanud vastutuse." </eesti>
<inglise>"I swear to be faithful to the constitutional order of Estonia and to perform in a conscientious and accurate manner the functions which the office entrusted to me requires.I am aware that the law prescribes liability for a breach of duties or the public service code of ethics." </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vande andja kirjutab vandetekstile alla, m&auml;rkides &auml;ra ka vande andmise kuup&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who takes the oath shall sign the text of the oath, also indicating the date of taking the oath. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametivande teksti hoitakse koos teenistuslehega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The text of the oath of office shall be held together with the service record. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud ametivannet ei pea andma ametnik, kes on andnud politseivande. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official who has taken the police oath is not required to take the oath of office specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.05.98 j&otilde;ust.15.06.98 - RT I 1998, 50, 753) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.05.98 entered into force 15.06.98 - RT I 1998, 50, 753) </inglise>
<eesti>2. jaotis. </eesti>
<inglise>Subdivision 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi korras teenistusse v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Employment in service by way of competition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi korras t&auml;idetavad ametikohad </eesti>
<inglise>Positions filled by way of competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiteenistujate ametinimetuste ja palgaastmestiku seaduse paragrahvi 4 l. l&otilde;ike punktis l nimetatud k&otilde;rgemaid ametnikke nimetatakse ametisse avaliku konkursi alusel, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 30 loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Higher officials specified in clause 4 (1) 1) of the State Public Servants Official Titles and Salary Scale Act shall be appointed to office on the basis of a public competition, except in the cases specified in &sect; 30 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuse juhi otsusel v&otilde;ib avaliku konkursi v&auml;lja kuulutada ka muude ametikohtade t&auml;itmiseks vastavas ametiasutuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) By the decision of the head of a state or local government administrative agency, a public competition may also be announced to fill other positions in the corresponding administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursita teenistusse v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Employment in service without competition </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku konkursita v&otilde;ib ametisse nimetada: </eesti>
<inglise>The following may be appointed to office without a public competition: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Riigikogu Kantselei, Vabariigi Presidendi Kantselei, &Otilde;iguskantsleri Kantselei, Riigikohtu ja Riigikontrolli ametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>1) officials of the Chancellery of the Riigikogu, the Office of the President of the Republic, the Office of the Legal Chancellor, the Supreme Court and the State Audit Office; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt ametisse nimetatavaid ametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>2) officials appointed to office by the Government of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>3) peaministri ja ministrite n&otilde;unikke ja abisid (paragrahv 21 lg. 2 p. 5) ning peaministri poolt ametisse nimetatavaid isikuid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) advisers and assistants to the Prime Minister and ministers (clause 21 (2) 5)), or officials appointed to office by the Prime Minister; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ajutisi asendajaid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) temporary substitutes; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kohuset&auml;itjaid konkursi korras t&auml;idetavale vabale ametikohale; </eesti>
<inglise>5) acting officials, to vacant positions to be filled by way of competition; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ametialase edutamise korras; </eesti>
<inglise>6) persons, by way of promotion; </inglise>
<eesti>7) (v&auml;lja j&auml;etud - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>7) (omitted - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi v&auml;ljakuulutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Announcement of competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avaliku konkursi ametniku vabale ametikohale kuulutab ametlikus v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded v&auml;lja riigisekret&auml;r vastava ametniku ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omava isiku ettepanekul, andes kandidaatidele avalduse esitamiseks aega v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat teadaande avaldamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The State Secretary shall, in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded (3), announce a public competition for a vacant position of an official, on the proposal of a person authorised to appoint the corresponding official, allowing candidates at least two weeks after the date of publication of the notice for submission of their applications. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.01.99 j&otilde;ust.01.03.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 155) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.01.99 entered into force 01.03.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 155) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkursiteadaanne peab sisaldama v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A notice of competition shall contain at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametiasutuse ja konkursi korras t&auml;idetava ametikoha nimetust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the administrative agency and title of the position to be filled by way of competition; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kandidaadile esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the requirements set for applicants; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametipalga suurust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the amount of salary; </inglise>
<eesti>4) avalduse ja muude vajalike dokumentide esitamise t&auml;htaega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the deadline for submission of an application and other necessary documents; </inglise>
<eesti>5) konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni aadressi; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the address of the competition and evaluation committee; </inglise>
<eesti>6) konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni koosoleku aega. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the date and time of meeting of the competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni koosolek toimub mitte varem kui kolme n&auml;dala m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel, arvates konkursiteadaande avaldamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The meeting of a competition and evaluation committee shall be held not earlier than three weeks after the date of publication of the notice of competition. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Dokumentide esitamine konkursil osalemiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Submission of documents for participation in competition </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursil osalemise avaldus esitatakse koos k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 23 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 2-4 ja 7 loetletud dokumentidega konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni (paragrahv 93) nimele. </eesti>
<inglise>An application for participation in a competition shall be submitted together with documents set out in clauses 23 (1) 2) -4) and 7) of this Act and shall be addressed to the competition and evaluation committee (&sect; 93). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursil osalejate hindamine </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment of participants in competition </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon hindab kandidaatide vastavust ametikoha t&auml;itmiseks esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele, kuulab vajadusel &auml;ra isiku, kellel on &otilde;igus nimetada sellele ametikohale, ja teeb oma otsuse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 97 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A competition and evaluation committee shall assess whether the applicants meet the requirements set for the position, shall hear, where necessary, a person authorised to make appointments to that position and shall make its decision pursuant to procedure provided for in &sect; 97 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi tulemuste teatavakstegemine </eesti>
<inglise>Announcement of competition results </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon esitab ametikohale nimetamiseks &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitu kandidaati v&otilde;i loobub kandidaadi esitamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A competition and evaluation committee shall present one candidate or several candidates for a position or decline to present a candidate. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees, tema &auml;raolekul aseesimees v&otilde;i selleks volitatud liige teatab hiljemalt otsuse tegemise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval kirjalikult igale kandidaadile tema kohta tehtud otsuse ning ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omavale isikule andmed esitatud kandidaatide kohta v&otilde;i kandidaatide esitamisest loobumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The chairman of a competition and evaluation committee or, in his or her absence, the deputy chairman or a duly authorised member shall, not later than on the working day following the date the decision is made, notify each applicant in writing of the decision concerning him or her and the person with appointment authority of the information regarding the presented candidates or of declining to present any candidates. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Esitatud kandidaadi ametisse nimetamine v&otilde;i reservi arvamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment to office or assignment to reserve of presented candidate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametikohale nimetamiseks esitatud kandidaadid esitavad kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsuse teatavakssaamise p&auml;evast, ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omavale isikule kirjaliku avalduse, elulookirjelduse, omak&auml;elise kinnituse, et nad vastavad teenistusse astumiseks seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele, k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 23 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 4-6 nimetatud dokumentide koopiad ning muud seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel n&otilde;utavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Candidates presented for a position shall submit to a person with appointment authority, within two weeks after receipt of the decision of a competition and evaluation committee, an application in writing, a curriculum vitae, a confirmation under the hand of the applicant that he or she meets the requirements for the service provided by law, copies of the documents specified in clauses 23 (1) 4) - 6) of this Act and other documents required by law or pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametikohale nimetamise &otilde;igust omav isik nimetab konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni poolt ametisse nimetamiseks esitatud nende isikute hulgast, kes t&auml;itsid k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud tingimused, ametisse &uuml;he kandidaadi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person with appointment authority shall appoint to office one of the candidates from among the persons who were presented for the position by a competition and evaluation committee and who fulfilled the conditions specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametikohale nimetamisel ja ametisse astumisel j&auml;rgitakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 23-25. </eesti>
<inglise>Sections 23 - 25 of this Act shall be observed in the appointment to and assumption of office. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikutele, keda ametisse ei nimetatud, teatab ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omav isik hiljemalt ametisse nimetatud isiku ametisse astumise p&auml;eval kirjalikult ja motiveeritult nende ametisse mittenimetamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons who are not appointed to office shall be notified thereof in writing, with a reasoned explanation, by the person with appointment authority not later than on the date on which the person appointed to office assumes office. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametikohale nimetamiseks esitatud kandidaat, keda temast s&otilde;ltumatutel p&otilde;hjustel ei nimetatud ametisse ja kes ei ole ametnik, v&otilde;ib kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omavalt isikult teate saamise p&auml;evast, esitada reservi arvamise avalduse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 138 punktile 3. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A candidate who is presented for a position but who is not appointed to office for reasons independent of him or her and who is not an official may submit, within two weeks after receipt of the notice from the person with appointment authority, an application for his or her assignment to the reserve pursuant to clause 138 3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi luhtumine </eesti>
<inglise>Failure of competition </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurss loetakse luhtunuks, kui sellel osalemiseks ei esitatud &uuml;htegi avaldust, samuti siis, kui konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon loobus ametikohale nimetamiseks kandidaadi esitamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>A competition shall be considered failed if no applications are submitted for participation in the competition or if a competition and evaluation committee declines to present a candidate for a position. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of Public Servant </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga maksmine ja lisatasu teenistusaastate eest </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of salary and additional remuneration for years of service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistujal on &otilde;igus saada palka alates teenistusse astumise p&auml;evast kuni teenistusest vabastamise p&auml;evani. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant shall be entitled to receive a salary from the date of entry into the service until the date of release from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiametnikule makstakse lisatasu teenistusaastate eest j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State officials shall receive additional remuneration for years of service as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alates 5-aastasest teenistusstaa&zcaron;ist - 5% ametipalgast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) from 5 years of service, 5 per cent of the salary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 10-15-aastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral - 10% ametipalgast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for 10 -15 years of service, 10 per cent of the salary; </inglise>
<eesti>3) alates 15-aastasest teenistusstaa&zcaron;ist - 15% ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>3) from 15 years of service, 15 per cent of the salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tasu v&otilde;ib j&auml;tta maksmata v&otilde;i selle suurust v&otilde;ib v&auml;hendada ametniku distsiplinaarkaristuse kehtivuse ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Remuneration provided for in subsection (2) of this section may remain unpaid, or the amount thereof may be decreased during the time a disciplinary punishment of the state official is in force. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Palka makstakse palgaseaduses (RT I 1994, 11, 154; 1995, 12, 120; 1999, 29, 397; 2000, 10, 59; 40, 248) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Salary shall be paid pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Wages Act (RT I 1994, 11, 154; 1995, 12, 120; 1999, 29, 397; 2000, 10, 59; 40, 248). </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisatasu akadeemilise kraadi eest </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration for academic degree </inglise>
<eesti>Akadeemilise kraadiga riigiametnikule makstakse lisatasu: </eesti>
<inglise>A state official with an academic degree shall receive additional remuneration as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) magistrikraadi eest - 10% ametipalgast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for a master's degree, 10 per cent of the salary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) doktorikraadi v&otilde;i sellega v&otilde;rdsustatud kraadi eest - 20% ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>2) for a doctor's degree or equivalent, 20 per cent of the salary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisatasu v&otilde;&otilde;rkeelte valdamise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration for proficiency in foreign languages </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiametnikule, kes valdab teda ametisse nimetanud isiku v&otilde;i ametiasutuse poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud ulatuses v&auml;hemalt kolme v&otilde;&otilde;rkeelt ja nende keelte kasutamine on teenistuses vajalik, makstakse kolmanda ja iga j&auml;rgmise v&otilde;&otilde;rkeele eest lisatasuna 10 protsenti ametipalgast, kuid kokku mitte &uuml;le 30 protsendi. </eesti>
<inglise>A state official who is proficient in at least three foreign languages, to the extent specified by a person or administrative agency who has appointed him or her to office, and the use of these languages is required in the service, shall receive 10 per cent of his or her salary as additional remuneration for the third and each subsequent foreign language, but not more than a total of 30 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Lisatasu riigisaladuse ja salastatud teabekandjate t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration for processing state secrets or classified media </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistujale (v&auml;lja arvatud julgeolekuasutuse ametnik), kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab ametikohal, millel t&ouml;&ouml;tamise eeltingimuseks on riigisaladusele juurdep&auml;&auml;su loa omamine, makstakse lisatasu kuni 50 protsenti tema ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>A public servant (except an official of a security authority) employed in a position where a permit for access to state secrets is a prerequisite for employment shall receive 50 per cent of his or her salary as additional remuneration. </inglise>
<eesti>(26.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 271; 20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 271; 20.12.2000 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 17) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusl&auml;hetusse saatmine ja l&auml;hetuskulude h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Sending on official travel and reimbursement of travel expenses </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistujal on &otilde;igus teenistusl&auml;hetuse kulude h&uuml;vitamisele seaduse v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimustel, ulatuses ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant shall be entitled to reimbursement of official travel expenses under conditions, to the extent and pursuant to procedure established by law or a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistusl&auml;hetuse ajaks s&auml;ilitatakse teenistujale ameti- v&otilde;i abiteenistuskoht ja palk. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The position or support staff position and the salary of a public servant shall be retained for the duration of official travel. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistusl&auml;hetusse ei ole lubatud saata rasedat, samuti isikut, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi, invaliidi lapseeast v&otilde;i alla kolmeaastast last, ilma isiku n&otilde;usolekuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A pregnant woman or a person raising a disabled child, one who is disabled from childhood or child under three years of age shall not be permitted to be sent on official travel without the person's consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitus riigiametniku nimetamisel teises paikkonnas asuvale ametikohale </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation upon appointment of state official to position in another locality </inglise>
<eesti>Teises paikkonnas asuvale ametikohale nimetamise korral makstakse riigiametnikule h&uuml;vitusena &uuml;he kuu ametipalk uuel ametikohal, kui see on suurem riigiametniku viimasest ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon appointment to a position in another locality, a state official shall be paid his or her one month's salary in the new position as compensation if this is greater than the last salary of the state official. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ametipalk uuel ametikohal on v&auml;iksem riigiametniku viimasest ametipalgast, siis makstakse h&uuml;vitusena riigiametniku viimase ametipalga suurune summa. </eesti>
<inglise>If in the new position the salary is smaller than the last salary of the state official, he or she shall be paid an amount which equals to the last salary of the state official as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisaks h&uuml;vitatakse ametniku ja tema perekonnaliikmete s&otilde;idu- ja varaveokulud Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimustel, ulatuses ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>In addition, the travel and moving expenses of the official and of his or her family members shall be reimbursed under conditions, to the extent and pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idukulude h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reimbursement of travel expenses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(1) (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isikliku s&otilde;iduki ametis&otilde;itudeks kasutamise kulud h&uuml;vitatakse ametnikule Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimustel, ulatuses ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall be reimbursed for expenses relating to the use of a personal vehicle for business travel under conditions, to the extent and pursuant to procedure established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisl&auml;hetus </eesti>
<inglise>Business travel abroad </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lisl&auml;hetuseks loetakse teenistuja l&auml;hetamist v&auml;lisriiki. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The sending of a public servant to a foreign state shall be considered business travel abroad. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa ministeeriumi valitsemisala asutuse juhi v&auml;lisl&auml;hetuseks annab kantsler ministri teadmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Permission for business travel abroad shall be granted to the head of an agency within the area of government of a ministry by the secretary general, with the knowledge of the minister. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.96 j&otilde;ust.29.02.96 - RT I 1996, 15, 265) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.96 entered into force 29.02.96 - RT I 1996, 15, 265) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistuja v&auml;lisl&auml;hetusse saatmise korra, v&auml;lisl&auml;hetustasu ning h&uuml;vitiste suuruse ja nende maksmise korra, samuti muud sotsiaalsed tagatised kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for sending a public servant on business travel abroad, the amount of remuneration for business travel abroad, the amount of compensation and the procedure for the payment thereof, and other social guarantees shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Working and rest time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistujal on kahe puhkep&auml;evaga viiep&auml;evane t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant shall have a five-day working week with two days off. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistuja t&ouml;&ouml;aeg ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 40 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The working time of a public servant shall not exceed forty hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistuja t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaeg m&auml;&auml;ratakse t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seaduse (RT I 1994, 2, 12; 1995, 12, 120; 2001, 21, 114) alusel, arvestades k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja avalikku teenistust reguleerivate eriseadustega s&auml;testatud erisusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The working and rest time of a public servant shall be specified pursuant to the Working and Rest Time Act (RT I 1994, 2, 12; 1995, 12, 120; 2110, 21, 114), considering the differences provided by this Act and laws specifically regulating the public service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkus ja puhkusetasu </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday and holiday pay </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikul on &otilde;igus puhkuseseaduses (RT 1992, 37, 481; 1993, 10, 150; 1994, 84, 1474; 1995, 16, 228; 1997, 74, 1229; 93, 1560; 1999, 82, 749) s&auml;testatud 35-kalendrip&auml;evasele p&otilde;hipuhkusele ja teistele puhkustele puhkuseseaduses ja k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be entitled to a base holiday of thirty-five calendar days provided for in the Holiday Act (RT 1992, 37, 481; 1993, 10, 150; 1994, 84, 1474; 1995, 16, 228; 1997, 74, 1229; 93, 1560; 1999, 82, 749) and to other holidays under conditions and pursuant to procedure provided for in the Holiday Act and this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;hemalt kolmeaastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral antakse ametnikule kolmanda ja iga j&auml;rgmise aasta eest &uuml;ks p&auml;ev lisapuhkust, kuid kokku mitte rohkem kui 10 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of at least three years of service, an official shall be granted one day of additional holiday for the third and each subsequent year, but not more than a total of ten calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse kehtivuse ajal v&otilde;ib lisapuhkust v&auml;hendada v&otilde;i j&auml;tta andmata. </eesti>
<inglise>During the time a disciplinary punishment is in force, additional holidays may be decreased or withheld. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkusetasu makstakse hiljemalt eelviimasel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval enne puhkuse algust t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Holiday pay shall be paid in full not later than on the penultimate working day before commencement of a holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametnik, kellele ei makstud puhkusetasu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud ajal, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda puhkuse pikendamist puhkusetasu maksmisega viivitatud aja v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official to whom holiday pay is not paid at the time provided for in subsection (3) of this section may demand an extension of his or her holiday with holiday pay equal to the period of time the holiday pay is delayed. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetoetus </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday benefit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistujale v&otilde;ib maksta p&otilde;hipuhkusega seoses puhkusetoetust kuni &uuml;he kuu ametipalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant may be paid a holiday benefit of up to one month's salary in connection with his or her base holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetoetuse maksmise korral tuleb puhkusetoetust maksta k&otilde;ikidele teenistujatele v&otilde;rdsetel alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon payment of holiday benefits, the holiday benefits shall be paid to all public servants on equal bases. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Puhkuse &uuml;leviimisel j&auml;rgmisele t&ouml;&ouml;aastale makstakse puhkusetoetust ka eelmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) If a holiday is carried over to the following working year, a holiday benefit shall also be paid for the preceding working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui puhkus antakse osadena, siis makstakse kogu puhkusetoetus v&auml;lja puhkuse esimese osa kasutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a holiday is granted in parts, the whole holiday benefit shall be paid upon the use of the first part of the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarkaristuse kehtivuse ajal puhkusetoetust ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) During the time a disciplinary punishment is in force, a holiday benefit shall not be paid. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Puhkusetoetus makstakse v&auml;lja teenistuja valikul kas koos puhkusetasuga v&otilde;i esimesel palgap&auml;eval p&auml;rast puhkuselt naasmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A holiday benefit shall be paid, as chosen by the public servant, either together with the holiday pay or on the first pay day after return from holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku &uuml;leviimine ja talle ametikohav&auml;liste &uuml;lesannete andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of official and assignment of functions beyond scope of his or her position </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teisele ametikohale &uuml;leviimine, samuti talle ametikohav&auml;liste &uuml;lesannete andmine on lubatud ainult ametniku kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 60, 61 ja 64 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>The transfer of an official to another position, or the assignment to him or her of functions beyond the scope of his or her position is permitted only with the written consent of the official, except in the cases provided for in &sect;&sect; 60, 61 and 64 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teise paikkonda &uuml;leviimine on lubatud ainult ametniku kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 61 s&auml;testatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>The transfer of an official to another locality is permitted only with the written consent of the official, except in the case provided for in &sect; 61 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tasustamine ametniku ebaseadusliku &uuml;leviimise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration in case of unlawful transfer of official </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnikul on &otilde;igus saada senist palka ebaseadusliku &uuml;leviimise kogu aja eest, kui tal sel ajal ei lubatud j&auml;tkata seniste &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmist ja ta teatas kirjalikult ebaseadusliku korralduse teinud isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele &uuml;leviimise ebaseaduslikkusest. </eesti>
<inglise>An official shall be entitled to receive his or her former salary for the whole period of unlawful transfer if he or she is not permitted to continue to perform his or her former functions and if he or she notifies in writing the person who or the administrative agency which issued the unlawful order of the unlawfulness of the transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leviimine tervislikel p&otilde;hjustel </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer for health reasons </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnikul, kellele arsti otsuse alusel on senisel ametikohal teenistuse j&auml;tkamine tervise t&otilde;ttu vastun&auml;idustatud, on &otilde;igus saada samas ametiasutuses tervisele vastav ametikoht, v&auml;lja arvatud konkursi korras t&auml;idetav ametikoht. </eesti>
<inglise>An official who, by the decision of a doctor, is advised not to continue in his or her position for health reasons shall be entitled to receive a position suitable to his or her state of health in the same administrative agency, except a position to be filled by way of competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ametiasutuses ei ole sellist ametikohta v&otilde;i kui ametnik ei vasta sellise ametikoha t&auml;itmiseks esitatavatele muudele n&otilde;uetele, vabastatakse ta teenistusest k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 117 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 5 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>If there is no such position available in the administrative agency or if the official does not meet other requirements set for filling that position, the official shall be released from the service pursuant to clause 117 (1) 5) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistustingimuste ajutine kergendamine ja ametniku ajutine &uuml;leviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of conditions of service and temporary transfer of official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikul on arsti otsuse alusel &otilde;igus teenistustingimuste ajutisele kergendamisele v&otilde;i ajutisele &uuml;leviimisele terviseseisundile vastavale ametikohale, v&auml;lja arvatud konkursi korras t&auml;idetavale ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be entitled, by the decision of a doctor, to the temporary easement of his or her conditions of service or to a temporary transfer to a position suitable to his or her state of health, except a position to be filled by way of competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnikule makstakse uuele ametikohale vastavat ametipalka, kui see on ametniku senisest ametipalgast suurem, ja lisatasusid, millele ametnikul on &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>The official shall be paid a salary appropriate to the new position if it is higher than his or her former salary, and the additional remuneration which the official is entitled to receive. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui uuele ametikohale vastav ametipalk on ametniku senisest ametipalgast v&auml;iksem, s&auml;ilitatakse ametnikule senine palk. </eesti>
<inglise>If the salary corresponding to the new position is lower than the official's former salary, he or she shall retain the former salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud teenistustingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i &uuml;leviimise v&otilde;imatuse korral vabastatakse ametnik ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest arsti otsuses m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If easement of conditions of service or transfer provided for in subsection (1) of this section is impossible, an official shall be released from the performance of his or her functions until the expiry of the leave noted in the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle aja eest makstakse ametnikule senist palka. </eesti>
<inglise>The official shall be paid his or her former salary for that period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistustingimuste ajutine kergendamine ja ametniku ajutine &uuml;leviimine raseduse ajaks </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of conditions of service and temporary transfer of official during pregnancy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikul on tema raseduse ajaks arsti vormistatud haiguslehe alusel &otilde;igus teenistustingimuste ajutisele kergendamisele v&otilde;i ajutisele &uuml;leviimisele teisele ametikohale, v&auml;lja arvatud konkursi korras t&auml;idetavale ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) During pregnancy, an official shall be entitled, based on a certificate for sick leave prepared by a doctor, to the temporary easement of her conditions of service or to a temporary transfer to another position, except a position to be filled by way of competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgavahe h&uuml;vitatakse Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999; 7, 113; 2000, 84, 536) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The difference in wages shall be compensated pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 2000, 84, 536). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud teenistustingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i &uuml;leviimise v&otilde;imatuse korral vabastatakse ametnik haiguslehel n&auml;idatud ajaks ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest ja makstakse kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitist Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras." </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the easement of conditions of service or transfer provided for in subsection (1) of this section is impossible, an official shall be released from the performance of her functions for the period prescribed in the certificate for sick leave and shall be paid a compulsory health insurance benefit pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla kolmeaastast last kasvatava ametniku soodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Benefits for official raising disabled child or child under three years of age </inglise>
<eesti>Soodustused, mis vastavalt seadusele on lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla kolmeaastast last kasvataval naisel, laienevad ka meesametnikule, kes &uuml;ksi kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla kolmeaastast last, samuti ametnikule, kes on alla kolmeaastase lapse v&otilde;i lapsinvaliidi eestkostjaks. </eesti>
<inglise>Benefits enjoyed pursuant to law by a woman raising a disabled child or child under 3 years of age shall also extend to a male official who, alone, is raising a disabled child or child under 3 years of age and to an official who is the guardian of a disabled child or child under 3 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekulude h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reimbursement of educational expenses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikul, kes sai riiklikku &otilde;ppelaenu ja p&auml;rast &otilde;ppeasutuse l&otilde;petamist astus riigiteenistusse, on &otilde;igus riikliku &otilde;ppelaenu kustutamisele Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimustel, ulatuses ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who receives a state educational loan and who, after graduating from an educational institution, enters into the state public service shall be entitled to the forgiveness of his or her state educational loan under conditions, to the extent and pursuant to procedure provided by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riiklikus k&otilde;rgkoolis &otilde;ppiv Eesti kodanik, kelle m&otilde;lemal v&otilde;i &uuml;hel vanemal on v&otilde;i oli v&auml;hemalt l5-aastane teenistusstaa&zcaron; riigiametnikuna, on &otilde;igus saada &otilde;ppemaksu h&uuml;vitist riigieelarve vahenditest Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korras, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui nimetatud staa&zcaron; on katkenud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 154 s&auml;testatud asjaoludel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An Estonian citizen studying at a public institution of higher education whose both parents have been or were or whose one parent has been or was employed in the service as a state official for at least fifteen years has the right to the reimbursement of tuition fees from state budget funds pursuant to procedure established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic, except if the service is interrupted due to the circumstances provided for in &sect; 154 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Samasugune &otilde;igus on ka isikul, kelle v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks riigiteenistuses olnud vanematest v&otilde;i riigiteenistuses olnud abikaasa invaliidistus v&otilde;i suri t&ouml;&ouml;vigastuse, kutsehaiguse, tema suhtes teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&otilde;ttu toimepandud r&uuml;nde v&otilde;i kuriteo t&otilde;kestamise tagaj&auml;rjel. </eesti>
<inglise>A person of whose parents at least one or whose spouse employed in the state public service becomes disabled or dies as a result of a work injury, an occupational disease, an attack made against him or her due to his or her functions, or as a result of the combating of a criminal offence also has this right. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppepuhkus t&ouml;&ouml;alaseks eneset&auml;iendamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Study leave for professional development </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiametnikule antakse &uuml;ks kord viie aasta jooksul kuni kolmeks kuuks &otilde;ppepuhkust t&ouml;&ouml;alaseks eneset&auml;iendamiseks ametipalga s&auml;ilitamisega t&auml;iskasvanute koolituse seaduses (RT I 1993, 74, 1054; 1998, 71, 1200; 1999, 10, 150; 60, 617) kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A state official shall be granted a study leave with pay for up to three months once every five years for professional development pursuant to procedure established in the Adult Education Act (RT I 1993, 74, 1054; 1998, 71, 1200; 1999, 10, 150; 60, 617). </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Eluruumi kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of dwelling </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnikule antakse v&otilde;imaluse korral t&ouml;&ouml;andja eluruum v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitatakse muu eluruumi kasutamiskulud, kui ametnik nimetatakse teises paikkonnas asuvale ametikohale v&otilde;i kui tal ametiasutuse asukohas ei ole omaette eluruumi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state official shall be provided with a dwelling by the employer, where possible, or shall be compensated for the expenses incurred for using another dwelling if the official is appointed to a position located in another locality or if the official has no dwelling of his or her own in the location of the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametikohtade loetelu, kus h&uuml;vitatakse muu eluruumi kasutamiskulud, ning kasutamiskulude piirm&auml;&auml;rad kehtestatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The list of positions where the expenses incurred for using another dwelling are compensated for and the limits of such expenses shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Toitlustamise tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Ensurance of catering </inglise>
<eesti>Riigipiiril asuvas tollipunktis sanitaar-, karantiini-, veterinaar-, toidu-, f&uuml;tosanitaar- v&otilde;i tollikontrolli teostavale riigiametnikule tagatakse toitlustamine teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>A state official exercising sanitary control, quarantine control, veterinary control, food control, plant health control or customs control at a customs post at the state border shall be provided with catering services during the time when he or she performs his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus teenistuja surma korral v&otilde;i invaliidistumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Allowance upon death or disability of public servant </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja surma korral tema suhtes teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&otilde;ttu toimepandud r&uuml;nde v&otilde;i kuriteo t&otilde;kestamise tagaj&auml;rjel makstakse tema &uuml;lalpidamisel olnud perekonnaliikmetele &uuml;hekordset toetust surnud isiku 10 aasta ametipalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the death of a public servant as a result of an attack against him or her due to his or her functions, or as a result of the combating of a criminal offence, those family members of the public servant who were maintained by him or her shall be paid a single allowance to the extent of ten years' salary of the deceased person. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugustel asjaoludel surnud isiku matused korraldatakse riigi kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>Funeral expenses of a person deceased under such circumstances shall be borne by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud asjaoludel invaliidistunud teenistujale makstakse &uuml;hekordset toetust: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public servant who becomes disabled under the circumstances provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be paid a single allowance upon: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osalise kaotuse korral - tema &uuml;he aasta ametipalga ulatuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) partial loss of capacity for work, to the extent of his or her one year's salary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime t&auml;ieliku kaotuse korral - tema viie aasta ametipalga ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>2) total loss of capacity for work, to the extent of his or her five years' salary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku vanaduspension </eesti>
<inglise>Old-age pension of official </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikule kindlustatakse riiklik vanaduspension k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud eranditega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be ensured a state old-age pension with the exceptions provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riiklikke vanaduspensione suurendatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State old-age pensions shall be increased as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 10 - 15-aastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral - 10 % v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for 10 - 15 years of service, by 10 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 16 - 20-aastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral - 20 % v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for 16 - 20 years of service, by 20 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 21 - 25-aastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral - 25 % v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for 21 - 25 years of service, by 25 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>4) 26 - 30-aastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral - 40 % v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise>4) for 26 - 30 years of service, by 40 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &uuml;le 30-aastase teenistusstaa&zcaron;i korral - 50 % v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>5) for more than 30 years of service, by 50 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kulutused, mis tulenevad k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud vanaduspensionide suurendamisest, kaetakse riigieelarve vahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Expenditure resulting from an increase in old-age pension provided for in subsection (2) of this section shall be covered from state budget funds. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku muud teenistusalased &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Other service-related rights of official </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnikul on suhetes oma t&ouml;&ouml;andja ning sotsiaalkindlustust v&otilde;i -hooldust teostava asutusega k&otilde;ik &otilde;igused, mis on ette n&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tavale isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>An official has all the rights prescribed for a person employed under an employment contract in the official's relationship with his or her employer and with an agency responsible for social insurance or care. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandid ja t&auml;iendavad &otilde;igused s&auml;testatakse k&auml;esoleva ja muude avalikku teenistust reguleerivate seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>Exceptions and supplementary rights shall be provided by this Act and other laws regulating the public service. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmine ja &otilde;igusaktide j&auml;rgimise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Performance of duties and obligation to observe legislation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja peab oma teenistuskohustusi t&auml;itma t&auml;pselt, &otilde;igeaegselt, kohusetundlikult, otstarbekalt ja omakasup&uuml;&uuml;dmatult, l&auml;htudes avalikest huvidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant shall perform his or her duties in an accurate, timely and conscientious manner, expediently and without self-interest, pursuant to the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohustused on kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud k&auml;esoleva seaduse, muude seaduste, samuti m&auml;&auml;ruste ja ametijuhendite ning muude &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise>The duties of service are determined in this Act and other laws, regulations and job descriptions, and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmisel peab teenistuja samuti l&auml;htuma k&auml;esoleva seaduse lisas 1 toodud avaliku teenistuse eetikakoodeksist ning teistest, ametiasutuse siseselt kehtestatavatest eetikakoodeksitest. </eesti>
<inglise>A public servant shall also perform his or her duties pursuant to the public service code of ethics set out in Annex 1 to this Act and other codes of ethics established within the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Ametijuhendit v&otilde;ib muuta teenistuja n&otilde;usolekuta, kui ei muutu ametikoha eesm&auml;rk, p&otilde;hifunktsioon(id), n&otilde;utav erialane ettevalmistus ega teenistuja palk ja ametniku &uuml;lesannete maht oluliselt ei suurene. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) A job description may be changed without the consent of a public servant if the aim, main function(s) of and required professional training for the position and the salary of the public servant do not change, and the volume of functions of the official does not increase significantly. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistuja on kohustatud t&auml;itma teenistusse puutuvaid &otilde;igusakte ja korraldusi ning, ootamata erikorraldust, &uuml;lesandeid, mis tulenevad tema teenistuskohast, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvide 62 1. l&otilde;ikes ja 63 1. l&otilde;ikes loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public servant is required to implement legislation and orders pertaining to the service and, without waiting for a special order, to perform functions arising from his or her position, except in the cases set out in subsections 62 (1) and 63 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohast mittetulenevate korralduste t&auml;itmine </eesti>
<inglise>Execution of orders not arising from position </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja on kohustatud t&auml;itma vahetu &uuml;lemuse v&otilde;i ametiasutuse juhi &uuml;hekordseid teenistusalaseid korraldusi, mille t&auml;itmise kohustus ei tulene tema teenistuskohast, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvide 62 1. l&otilde;ikes ja 63 1. l&otilde;ikes loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant is required to execute one time service-related orders issued by his or her immediate superior or by the head of the administrative agency the obligation for the execution of which does not arise from the position of the public servant, except in the cases set out in subsections 62 (1) and 63 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametiasutuse juhi korraldusest peab teenistuja teatama oma vahetule &uuml;lemusele. </eesti>
<inglise>A public servant shall notify his or her immediate superior of an order issued by the head of the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud korralduse t&auml;itmine takistaks teenistuskohast tulenevate &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmist, peab teenistuja teatama sellest korralduse andjale ning korralduse kordamisel selle t&auml;itma. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the execution of an order specified in subsection (1) of this section should hinder the performance of functions arising from the position of a public servant, he or she shall notify the issuer of the order thereof and shall execute the order if it is repeated. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistus&uuml;lesannete hulka mittekuuluvate &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine </eesti>
<inglise>Performance of functions not belonging to functions of public servant </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja on ajutiselt kohustatud t&auml;itma ametiasutuse juhi antud &uuml;lesandeid, mis ei kuulu tema teenistus&uuml;lesannete hulka, kui niisuguste &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine on samas ametiasutuses vajalik loodus&otilde;nnetuse tagaj&auml;rgede kiireks k&otilde;rvaldamiseks v&otilde;i &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi, vara h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i riknemise kiireks &auml;rahoidmiseks, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmine on teenistujale tervise t&otilde;ttu vastun&auml;idustatud v&otilde;i ilmselt ei vasta tema v&otilde;imetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant is temporarily required to perform functions which are assigned to him or her by the head of the administrative agency but which do not belong to his or her functions if the performance of such functions in that administrative agency is necessary for the speedy elimination of the consequences of a natural disaster or for the speedy prevention of an accident, or destruction of or damage to property, except if the performance of the function by the public servant is not advisable for health reasons or if he or she is apparently incapable of performing the function. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistujale, kes ajutiselt vabastati seniste teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel, s&auml;ilitatakse senine palk. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public servant who is temporarily released from the performance of his or her current functions pursuant to subsection (1) of this section shall retain his or her current salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldused, mida on keelatud anda </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibited orders </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Keelatud on anda korraldust, mis: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The issuance of an order which: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on vastuolus &otilde;igusaktidega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) is in conflict with law; </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;letab korralduse andja v&otilde;imupiire; </eesti>
<inglise>2) exceeds the authority of the issuer of the order; </inglise>
<eesti>3) n&otilde;uab tegusid, mille sooritamiseks korralduse saajal puudub &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>3) requires acts which the recipient of the order has no right to perform shall be prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korralduse seaduslikkuses kahtlemisel on teenistuja kohustatud koheselt teatama korraldusest ja oma kahtlustest korralduse andjale ja tema k&otilde;rgemalseisvale &uuml;lemusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) When in doubt as to the legality of an order, a public servant is required to immediately notify the issuer of the order and the issuer's superior of the public servant's doubts. </inglise>
<eesti>Korralduse kirjalikul kordamisel tuleb korraldus t&auml;ita, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 63 1. l&otilde;ikes loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>If the order is repeated in writing, the order shall be executed, except in the cases set out in subsection 63 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohast mittetulenevate &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest keeldumise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Grounds for refusal to perform functions not arising from position </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvide 60 1. l&otilde;ikes, 61 1. l&otilde;ikes ja 62 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud kohustuste t&auml;itmisest keelduda, kui nende t&auml;itmine: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant may refuse to perform the duties provided for in subsections 60 (1), 61 (1) and 62 (2) of this Act if their performance: </inglise>
<eesti>1) oleks suunatud tema abikaasa v&otilde;i tema v&otilde;i abikaasa vanemate, vendade, &otilde;dede v&otilde;i laste v&otilde;i teiste talle l&auml;hedaste inimeste vastu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) would be directed against his or her spouse, his or her or the spouse's parents, brothers, sisters or children, or against other persons close to him or her; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on talle tervise t&otilde;ttu vastun&auml;idustatud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) is not advisable for health reasons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei v&otilde;imalda kasutada laste kasvatamiseks etten&auml;htud soodustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) does not allow the use of benefits prescribed for the raising of children; </inglise>
<eesti>4) eeldaks k&otilde;rgemat kvalifikatsiooni v&otilde;i teistsugust erialast ettevalmistust kui see, mis on antud teenistujal. </eesti>
<inglise>4) would require a higher qualification or different professional training than the given public servant has. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korralduse t&auml;itmisest keeldumisel peab teenistuja korralduse andjale kohe teatama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud asjaolust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the refusal to execute an order, a public servant must immediately notify the issuer of the order of a circumstance specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine </eesti>
<inglise>Performance of functions of absent official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puuduva ametniku ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omav isik v&otilde;ib ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku asendamiseks v&otilde;i vaba ametikoha t&auml;itmiseks edasil&uuml;kkamatutel juhtudel, kui ametiasutuse normaalne t&ouml;&ouml; oleks ametniku puudumise t&otilde;ttu takistatud ja asendaja v&otilde;i kohuset&auml;itja teenistusse v&otilde;tmine ei ole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i otstarbekas: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to replace a temporarily absent official or to fill a vacant position in cases of urgency if the normal operation of the administrative agency would be hindered due to the absence of the official and if employment of a substitute or an acting official is not possible or purposeful, a person with authority to appoint the absent official may: </inglise>
<eesti>1) jagada puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesanded teiste ametnike vahel, vabastamata neid oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) divide the functions of the absent official among other officials without releasing them from the performance of their own functions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) panna puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesanded teisele ametnikule, vabastades viimase tema &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) assign the functions of the absent official to another official, releasing the latter from the performance of his or her own functions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) panna puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesanded osaliselt teisele ametnikule, vabastamata teda oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>3) assign the functions of the absent official partly to another official, without releasing him or her from the performance of his or her own functions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud &uuml;lesannete ajutisest t&auml;itmisest keelduda, kui nende t&auml;itmine on talle tervise t&otilde;ttu vastun&auml;idustatud v&otilde;i eeldab k&otilde;rgemat kvalifikatsiooni v&otilde;i teistsugust erialast ettevalmistust kui see, mis on antud teenistujal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official may refuse to temporarily perform the functions specified in subsection (1) of this section if the performance thereof by the official is not advisable for health reasons or if this requires a higher qualification or different professional training than the given official has. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametnik ei v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel samas ametiasutuses puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;ita &uuml;le kahe kuu kalendriaastas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall not perform the functions of an absent official in the same administrative agency, pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, for more than two months per calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puuduvat ametnikku asendab tema koosseisuline aset&auml;itja v&otilde;i kui isik on andnud kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks pikema perioodi v&auml;ltel, siis seda t&auml;htaega ei kohaldata. </eesti>
<inglise>If the absent official is substituted by his or her deputy on the same staff or if a person grants written consent to perform the functions of the absent official during a longer period, this term does not apply. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametnikele, kes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 1 alusel asendavad puuduvat ametnikku, makstakse lisaks nende enda palgale lisatasu kuni puuduva ametniku ametipalga ulatuses proportsionaalselt neile pandud puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesannete hulgale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Officials who, pursuant to clause (1) 1) of this section, substitute for an absent official shall be paid, in addition to their own salary, additional remuneration of up to the salary of the absent official in proportion to the amount of functions of the absent official assigned to them. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ametnikule, kes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 2 alusel asendab puuduvat ametnikku, makstakse puuduva ametniku ametipalka, kui see on tema ametipalgast suurem, ja lisatasusid, millele asendajal on &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An official who, pursuant to clause (1) 2) of this section, substitutes for an absent official shall be paid the salary of the absent official if it is higher than his or her salary, and the additional remuneration which the substitute is entitled to receive. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puuduva ametniku ametipalk on asendaja ametipalgast v&auml;iksem, s&auml;ilitatakse asendajale tema senine palk. </eesti>
<inglise>If the salary of the absent official is lower than that of the substituting official, the substitute shall retain his or her former salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ametnikule, kes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 3 alusel asendab puuduvat ametnikku, makstakse lisaks tema enda palgale lisatasu kuni puuduva ametniku ametipalga ulatuses proportsionaalselt temale pandud puuduva ametniku &uuml;lesannete hulgale. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Officials who, pursuant to clause (1) 3) of this section, substitute for an absent official shall be paid, in addition to their own salary, additional remuneration of up to the salary of the absent official in proportion to the amount of functions of the absent official assigned to them. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Asjaajamise ja vara &uuml;leandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of operations and assets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja on kohustatud enne puhkusele minekut, samuti enne ameti- v&otilde;i abiteenistuskohalt vabastamist p&ouml;&ouml;rduma selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud isiku poole asjaajamise ja teenistuse t&otilde;ttu tema k&auml;tte usaldatud vara &uuml;leandmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant is required to turn to a designated person to transfer operations and assets entrusted to the public servant due to his or her office before going on holiday or before his or her release from office or support staff position. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud isik on kohustatud asjaajamise ja vara vastu v&otilde;tma. </eesti>
<inglise>The designated person is required to accept the operations and assets. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiteenistuja kohustused ja vastutus riigivara &uuml;leandmisel ja vastuv&otilde;tmisel s&auml;testatakse riigivara seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duties and liabilities of a state public servant upon the transfer and acceptance of state assets shall be provided by the State Assets Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaldamisele mittekuuluva teabe hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance of information not subject to disclosure </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuja peab nii teenistussuhte ajal kui ka p&auml;rast teenistusest vabastamist hoidma talle teenistuse t&otilde;ttu teatavaks saanud riigi- ja &auml;risaladust, teiste inimeste perekonna- ja eraellu puutuvaid andmeid ning muud konfidentsiaalsena saadud informatsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A public servant shall maintain a state or business secret which becomes known to him or her due to his or her office, information concerning the family and private life of others, and other information received in confidence during the time of the service relationship and after release from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>Kuulumine relvi valdavasse organisatsiooni </eesti>
<inglise>Membership in organisation which possesses weapons </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiteenistuja v&otilde;ib kuuluda relvi valdavasse, s&otilde;jav&auml;eliselt korraldatud v&otilde;i s&otilde;jalisi harjutusi harrastavasse organisatsiooni ainult teda ametisse nimetanud isiku v&otilde;i ametiasutuse loal ning vahetu &uuml;lemuse teadmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>A state public servant may belong to an organisation which possesses weapons, is militarily organised or performs military exercises only with the permission of the person or administrative agency who has appointed him or her to office and with the knowledge of his or her immediate superior. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud tingimus ei laiene kuulumisele riiklikesse organisatsioonidesse, jahimeeste &uuml;hendustesse ning &uuml;ldteadolevatesse ja -tunnustatud spordiorganisatsioonidesse. </eesti>
<inglise>This condition shall not extend to membership in state organisations, hunters' associations, and in generally known and recognised sports organisations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulundus&uuml;hendusse kuulumise piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on membership in commercial association </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnik ei v&otilde;i kuuluda tulundus&uuml;henduse alaliselt tegutsevasse juhtorganisse, kontroll- ega revisjoniorganisse, v&auml;lja arvatud riigi esindajana riigi v&otilde;i avalik-&otilde;igusliku isiku osalusega ettev&otilde;tte juhtimis- v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorganisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state official shall not belong to the permanent directing body or permanent control or audit body of a commercial association, except as a representative of the state to the directing or supervisory body of an enterprise with participation of the state or a person in public law. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi osalusega ettev&otilde;tte juhtimis- v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorganisse kuulumise eest riigiametnikule eritasu ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A state official shall not be paid additional remuneration for belonging to the directing or supervisory body of an enterprise with state participation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Erakonda kuulumise piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on political party membership </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiametnikud, v&auml;lja arvatud Riigikogu esimehe ja aseesimeeste n&otilde;unikud ja abid, Riigikogu fraktsioonide n&otilde;unikud ja konsultandid, peaministri ja ministrite n&otilde;unikud ja abid, ei v&otilde;i kuuluda erakonna alaliselt tegutsevasse juhtorganisse, kontroll- ega revisjoniorganisse. </eesti>
<inglise>State officials, except advisers and assistants to the Chairman and Deputy Chairmen of the Riigikogu, advisers and consultants to factions of the Riigikogu, and advisers and assistants to the Prime Minister and ministers shall not belong to the permanent directing body or permanent control or audit body of a political party. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirangud seoses teenistusalase j&auml;relevalvega </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions in connection with supervisory control </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnik ei v&otilde;i saada tulu &uuml;henduselt ega erakonnalt, mille &uuml;le ta teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise korras teostab j&auml;relevalvet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state official shall not receive income from an association or party over which he or she exercises supervision in performing his or her functions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnikule ei v&otilde;i panna kohustust teostada teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise korras j&auml;relevalvet tulundus&uuml;henduse &uuml;le, mille liikmeks ta on. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An obligation shall not be imposed on an official to exercise supervision, in performing his or her functions, over a commercial association of which he or she is a member. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Osalemine ettev&otilde;tluses </eesti>
<inglise>Participation in enterprise </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnik v&otilde;ib tegelda ettev&otilde;tlusega ainult teda ametisse nimetanud isiku v&otilde;i ametiasutuse loal, kui ettev&otilde;tlus ei takista teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmist ega kahjusta teenistuskoha mainet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state official may engage in enterprise only with the permission of the person or administrative agency who has appointed him or her to office if the enterprise does not hinder the performance of his or her functions or damage the reputation of his or her position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik ei v&otilde;i teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise korras teostada j&auml;relevalvet oma ettev&otilde;tluse &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall not exercise supervision over his or her own enterprise in performing his or her functions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tamine teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures </eesti>
<inglise>Employment with another employer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik v&otilde;ib teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;tada vahetu &uuml;lemuse poolt lubatud koormusega ja ajal, kui niisugune t&ouml;&ouml;tamine ei kahjusta teenistuskoha mainet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official may work for another employer with the work load and at the time permitted by his or her immediate superior, unless such employment damages the reputation of the official's position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik ei v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tada t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, kelle &uuml;le ta teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise korras teostab j&auml;relevalvet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall not work for an employer over whom he or she exercises supervision in performing his or her functions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirangud teenistusse v&otilde;i liikmeks astumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on entry into service and on membership </inglise>
<eesti>Ametist vabastatud riigiametnik ei v&otilde;i kolme aasta jooksul, arvates ametist vabastamise p&auml;evast, astuda selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja teenistusse v&otilde;i tulundus&uuml;henduse liikmeks, kelle &uuml;le ta viimase kolme aasta jooksul s&uuml;stemaatiliselt teostas j&auml;relevalvet. </eesti>
<inglise>A state official released from office shall not, within three years after the date of release from office, enter into the service of an employer over whom, or join a commercial association over which, he or she exercised supervision regularly within the last three years. </inglise>
<eesti>Ta ei v&otilde;i ka kolme aasta jooksul, arvates ametist vabastamise p&auml;evast, saada niisuguselt t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt v&otilde;i tulundus&uuml;henduselt tulu. </eesti>
<inglise>He or she shall also not receive income from such employer or commercial association within three years after the date of release from office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>Majanduslike huvide deklareerimise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to declare economic interest </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik on kohustatud esitama majanduslike huvide deklaratsiooni korruptsioonivastases seaduses s&auml;testatud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>An official is required to submit a declaration of his or her economic interests pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions provided for in the Anti-corruption Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.29.03.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 145) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.03.2000 entered into force 29.03.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 145) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirangud tehingute tegemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on conclusion of transaction </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistujal on keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant is prohibited from: </inglise>
<eesti>1) omandada tehingu tegemiseks tema k&auml;tte usaldatud selle isiku vara, kellega ta on t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistussuhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) acquiring assets which are entrusted to him or her for concluding a transaction and belong to a person with whom he or she is in employment or service relationship; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teha riigiasutust tehingus esindama &otilde;igustatud isikuna asjaomase ametiasutuse kaudu tehinguid riigiga v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutust tehingus esindama &otilde;igustatud isikuna asjaomase ametiasutuse kaudu tehinguid kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksusega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) concluding, as a person entitled to represent a state agency in transactions, transactions with the state through the administrative agency concerned, or concluding, as a person entitled to represent a local government agency in transactions, transactions with a local government through the administrative agency concerned; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teha riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse esindajana varalisi tehinguid korruptsioonivastase seaduse paragrahv 19 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud juriidiliste isikutega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with legal persons specified in subsection 19 (2) of the Anti-corruption Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teha riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse esindajana varalisi tehinguid mittetulundus&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i erakonnaga, mille liige ta on; </eesti>
<inglise>4) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with a non-profit association or political party of which he or she is a member; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teha riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse esindajana varalisi tehinguid selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja, &auml;ri&uuml;hingu, mittetulundus&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i erakonnaga, kelle tegevust ta kontrollib; </eesti>
<inglise>5) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with an employer, company, non-profit association or political party, over the activities of which he or she exercises supervision; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teha riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse esindajana varalisi tehinguid oma l&auml;hisugulaste, -h&otilde;imlaste v&otilde;i iseendaga. </eesti>
<inglise>6) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with his or her close relatives, close relatives by marriage, or himself or herself. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud keeldu rikkudes tehtud tehing on t&uuml;hine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Transactions concluded in violation of the prohibitions provided for in subsection (1) of this section are void. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametiasutuse sisekorraeeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>Internal Work Procedure Rules of Administrative Agency </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisekorraeeskirja sisu </eesti>
<inglise>Content of internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>Ametiasutuse sisekorraeeskirjaga m&auml;&auml;ratakse v&auml;hemalt allj&auml;rgnev: </eesti>
<inglise>Internal work procedure rules of an administrative agency shall specify at least the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;aja algus ja l&otilde;pp; </eesti>
<inglise>1) beginning and end of working time; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puhkamiseks ja einestamiseks antavad vaheajad ning t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evasisesed &uuml;ldised vaheajad; </eesti>
<inglise>2) breaks for rest and meals, and general breaks during a working day; </inglise>
<eesti>3) puhkep&auml;evadel, riigip&uuml;hadel ja p&auml;rast igap&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;aja l&otilde;ppu ametiasutuses viibimise tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>3) conditions and policies for being in the administrative agency on days off, public holidays and after the end of daily working time; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teenistusalaste korralduste teatavakstegemise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>4) procedure for the communication of service-related orders; </inglise>
<eesti>5) palgamaksmise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) time and place of payment of salary; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;kaitse ja tuleohutuse &uuml;ldjuhised; </eesti>
<inglise>6) general instructions for occupational health and safety and fire prevention; </inglise>
<eesti>7) &uuml;ldised k&auml;itumiseeskirjad ametiasutuses; </eesti>
<inglise>7) general rules of conduct in an administrative agency; </inglise>
<eesti>8) teenistusest puudumisest teatamise kord, kui teenistuja kasutab seadusega antud &otilde;igust puududa teenistusest tervislikel p&otilde;hjustel v&otilde;i kuni 14-aastase haige lapse hooldamiseks ilma haigus- v&otilde;i hooldusleheta. </eesti>
<inglise>8) procedure for the communication of an absence from the service if a public servant uses the right granted by law to be absent from the service for health reasons or to care for a child under fourteen years of age without a certificate for sick leave or care leave. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisekorraeeskirja kehtestamine ja tutvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of and access to internal work procedure rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiasutuse juht esitab sisekorraeeskirja projekti tutvumiseks ning ettepanekute ja m&auml;rkuste tegemiseks teenistujatele ja neid esindavatele organisatsioonidele v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat enne eeskirja kinnitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of an administrative agency shall present the draft internal work procedure rules for proposals and comments to public servants and to organisations representing them at least two weeks before approval of the rules. </inglise>
<eesti>Tehtud ettepanekud ja m&auml;rkused ei ole ametiasutuse juhile kohustuslikud, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui need l&auml;htuvad seadusest. </eesti>
<inglise>Proposals and comments made by public servants are not binding on the head of the administrative agency, except if they are based on law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametiasutuse sisekorraeeskirja kinnitab ametiasutuse juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Internal work procedure rules of an administrative agency shall be approved by the head of the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametiasutuse juht saadab sisekorraeeskirja &auml;rakirja p&auml;rast eeskirja kinnitamist ametiasutuse asukohaj&auml;rgsele t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorile ja teenistujaid esindavale organisatsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of an administrative agency shall send a copy of the internal work procedure rules to a labour inspector of the location of the administrative agency and to an organisation representing public servants in that location, after approval of the rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sisekorraeeskiri j&otilde;ustub kinnitamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval, kui eeskirjas ei n&auml;hta ette hilisemat j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The internal work procedure rules shall enter into force on the working day following the date of approval, unless a later date of entry into force is prescribed in the rules. </inglise>
<eesti>Eeskiri tehakse k&otilde;igile teenistujatele allkirja vastu teatavaks. </eesti>
<inglise>The rules shall be communicated to all public servants who shall confirm this with their signature. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ametiasutuse juht peab teenistusse v&otilde;tmisel tutvustama teenistujale sisekorraeeskirja, mille kohta teenistujalt v&otilde;etakse allkiri, ning tagama v&otilde;imaluse igal ajal eeskirjaga tutvuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the employment of a public servant, the head of an administrative agency shall inform the public servant of the internal work procedure rules, and the public servant shall confirm this with his or her signature; the head of the administrative agency shall ensure access to the rules at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutused, ametniku edutamine ja distsiplinaarvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Incentives, Promotion of Official and Liability to Disciplinary Action </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutused </eesti>
<inglise>Incentives </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 79. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 79. </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutuste liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of incentives </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kauaaegse teenistuse, samuti teenistuskohustuste v&otilde;i kodanikukohuse silmapaistvalt hea t&auml;itmise eest v&otilde;ib kohaldada j&auml;rgmisi ergutusi: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following incentives may be applied for long-term service and for noteworthy performance of duties or civil duty: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;nu avaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) expression of thanks; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rahalise preemia andmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) granting of a monetary award; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hinnalise kingituse andmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) giving of a valuable gift; </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&otilde;rgemale palgaastmele viimine. </eesti>
<inglise>4) advancement to a higher salary grade. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;heaegselt v&otilde;ib kohaldada mitut ergutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Several incentives may be applied simultaneously. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 4 s&auml;testatud ergutuse kasutamist ei v&auml;lista ametniku asumine k&otilde;ige k&otilde;rgemal palgaastmel, mis seadusega on sellele ametnikegrupile ette n&auml;htud, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui ametnik on k&otilde;ige k&otilde;rgemal palgaastmestikus s&auml;testatud palgaastmel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an official has the highest salary grade which is prescribed for the group of officials by law, it shall not preclude application of the incentive provided for in clause (1) 4) of this section unless the official has the highest salary grade provided for in the salary scale. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 80. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 80. </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutuse kohaldaja </eesti>
<inglise>Applier of incentive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistujale v&otilde;ib t&auml;nu avaldada tema &uuml;lemus, kellel on &otilde;igus anda k&auml;skkirja v&otilde;i korraldust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant may be thanked by his or her superior who has the right to issue a directive or order. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahalise preemia v&otilde;i hinnalise kingituse v&otilde;ib anda isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on antud teenistuja teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A monetary award may be granted or a valuable gift may be given by a person or administrative agency authorised to employ the given public servant. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&otilde;rgemale palgaastmele v&otilde;ib viia isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on antud teenistuja teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Advancement to a higher salary grade may be effected by a person or administrative agency authorised to employ the given public servant. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Motiveeritud ettepaneku ergutuse kohaldamiseks v&otilde;ib teha iga &uuml;lemus v&otilde;i ametiasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A reasoned proposal to apply an incentive may be made by any superior or administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 81. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 81. </inglise>
<eesti>Ergutuse vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of incentive </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ergutus vormistatakse motiveeritud k&auml;skkirja v&otilde;i korraldusega v&auml;hemalt kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b ergutuse kohaldajale, teise saab teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An incentive shall be made by way of a reasoned directive or order in at least two copies of which one is retained by the applier of the incentive and the other is given to the public servant. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ergutus kantakse teenistuslehele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An incentive shall be entered in the service record. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku edutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Promotion of Official </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 82. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 82. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku edutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Promotion of official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku edutamiseks loetakse ametniku nimetamist: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Promotion of an official means appointing the official: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&otilde;rgema p&otilde;higrupi ametikohale samas ametiasutuses v&otilde;i ametiasutuse haldusala piires; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to a position in a higher basic category of offices in the same administrative agency or within the jurisdiction of the administrative agency; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 29 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ametikohale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to a position specified in subsection 29 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametiasutuse, kus ametnik on teenistuses, k&otilde;rgemalseisva ametiasutuse sama p&otilde;higrupi ametikohale; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to a position in the same basic category of offices in an administrative agency superior to the administrative agency where the official is in the service; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuses juhtide p&otilde;higrupi ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>4) to a position belonging to the basic category of executive officers in a local government administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametniku edutamise &otilde;igus on isikul v&otilde;i ametiasutusel, kellel on &otilde;igus nimetada isik ametisse ametikohale, millele ametnik edutatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The person authorised to appoint an official to the position to which the official is being promoted, has the right to promote the official. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 83. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 83. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku edutamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for promotion of official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Edutada v&otilde;ib ametnikku, kes on senisel ametikohal olnud teenistuses v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud ning edutamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 29 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ametikohale on tunnistatud konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni poolt vastavaks sellele ametikohale, millele ametnik edutatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who has been in the service in his or her current position for at least six months and who, upon promotion to a position specified in subsection 29 (1) of this Act, has been declared suitable for the position to which he or she is being promoted by a competition and evaluation committee, may be promoted. </inglise>
<eesti>Motiveeritud ettepaneku ametniku edutamiseks v&otilde;ib teha tema &uuml;lemus, isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kes on ametniku ametisse nimetanud v&otilde;i kellel on &otilde;igus nimetada ametnik ametisse ametikohale, millele ametnik edutamiseks esitatakse, ja vastav konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>A reasoned proposal for the promotion of an official may be made by his or her superior, a person or an administrative agency who has appointed the official to office or who has the right to appoint an official to the position to which the official is being promoted, or by the corresponding competition and evaluation committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Edutamiseks on vajalik edutatava kirjalik n&otilde;usolek. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Written consent of the person to be promoted is required for promotion. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku edutamisel teise ametiasutusse on vajalik ametiasutuse, kus isik on teenistuses, juhi kirjalik n&otilde;usolek, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 82 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 3 nimetatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>Written consent of the head of the administrative agency where a person is in the service is required for promotion of the official to another administrative agency, except in the case specified in clause 82 (1) 3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mitme ametniku &uuml;hele ametikohale edutamiseks esitamise korral otsustab edutamise isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on &otilde;igus nimetada ametnik ametisse ametikohale, millele ametnik edutatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If several officials are presented for promotion to one position, promotion shall be decided by a person or administrative agency authorised to appoint an official to the position to which the official is being promoted. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametikohale mitteedutatuks osutunud ametnikele teatab edutamise &otilde;igust omav isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus sellest kirjalikult ja motiveeritult hiljemalt edutatuks osutunud ametniku edutamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>Officials not promoted to the position shall be notified thereof in writing, with a reasoned explanation, by the person or administrative agency who has the right of promotion not later than on the date of promotion of the promoted official. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku edutamisel teise ametiasutusse vabastatakse ta seniselt ametikohalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 127 1. l&otilde;ike alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon promotion of an official to another administrative agency, the official shall be released from his or her current position on the basis of subsection 127 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametnikku ei saa edutada distsiplinaarkaristuse kehtivuse ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official shall not be promoted during the time a disciplinary punishment is in force. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnike distsiplinaarvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability to Disciplinary Action of Officials </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 84. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 84. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teod </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary offences </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;tegudeks on: </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary offences are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teenistuskohustuste s&uuml;&uuml;line t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmine v&otilde;i mitten&otilde;uetekohane t&auml;itmine, sealhulgas teenistuses joobnuna viibimine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the wrongful non-performance or unsatisfactory performance of duties, including intoxication while in the service; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ametiasutusele s&uuml;&uuml;line varalise kahju tekitamine v&otilde;i niisuguse kahju tekkimise ohu s&uuml;&uuml;line loomine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the wrongful causing of damage to the property of an administrative agency or the wrongful causing of danger of such damage; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&auml;&auml;ritu tegu, s.o. s&uuml;&uuml;line tegu, mis on vastuolus &uuml;ldtunnustatud k&otilde;lblusnormidega, ametnikule esitatavate eetiliste n&otilde;uetega v&otilde;i diskrediteerib ametnikku v&otilde;i ametiasutust, s&otilde;ltumata sellest, kas niisugune tegu pandi toime teenistuses v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaspool teenistust. </eesti>
<inglise>3) an indecent act, that is, a wrongful act which is in conflict with generally recognised moral standards or ethic standards set for officials, or which discredits an official or administrative agency, regardless of whether the act is committed in or out of service. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 85. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 85. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristused </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary punishments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikele m&auml;&auml;ratavateks distsiplinaarkaristusteks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Disciplinary punishments imposed on officials are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) noomitus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a reprimand; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rahatrahv mitte &uuml;le ametniku 10-kordse p&auml;evapalga; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a fine not exceeding ten times the daily wage of an official; </inglise>
<eesti>3) palga maksmise peatamisega teenistusest k&otilde;rvaldamine mitte kauemaks kui 10 j&auml;rjestikuseks graafikuj&auml;rgseks t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) removal from the service with suspension of salary for not more than ten consecutive scheduled working days; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;leviimine madalamale palgaastmele kuni kolme astme v&otilde;rra mitte kauemaks kui &uuml;heks aastaks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) transfer to a lower salary grade by up to three grades for not longer than one year; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teenistusest vabastamine k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 118 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>5) release from the service pursuant to &sect; 118 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Iga s&uuml;&uuml;teo eest v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata ainult &uuml;he distsiplinaarkaristuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Only one disciplinary punishment may be imposed for each offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 4 s&auml;testatud distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramist ei v&auml;lista ametniku asumine k&otilde;ige madalamal palgaastmel, mis seadusega on sellele ametnikegrupile ette n&auml;htud, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui ametnik on k&otilde;ige madalamal palgaastmestikus s&auml;testatud palgaastmel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an official has the lowest salary grade which is prescribed for the group of officials by law, it shall not preclude imposition of the disciplinary punishment provided for in clause (1) 4) of this section unless the official has the lowest salary grade provided for in the salary scale. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 86. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 86. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;raja </eesti>
<inglise>Imposer of disciplinary punishment </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on isikul v&otilde;i ametiasutusel, kellel on antud ametniku ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>A person or administrative agency authorised to appoint the given official to office has the right to impose a disciplinary punishment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 87. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 87. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse kohaldamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for imposition of disciplinary punishment </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku distsiplinaarvastutusele v&otilde;tmisel kohaldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seaduse (RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 16, 228; 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2000, 102, 674) paragrahvide 6-13, 15, paragrahv 17 1., 2. ja 4.-6. l&otilde;iget ning paragrahvide 18, 19, paragrahv 20 1. ja 2. l&otilde;iget j&auml;rgmiste erisustega: </eesti>
<inglise>Upon bringing disciplinary action against an official, &sect;&sect; 6 - 13 and 15, subsections 17 (1), (2), (4) -(6), &sect;&sect; 18 and 19, and subsections 20 (1) and (2) of the Employees Disciplinary Punishments Act (RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 16, 228; 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2000, 102, 674) shall apply with the following differences: </inglise>
<eesti>1) paragrahvi 6 3. l&otilde;ikes osundatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise aluste asemel kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punktides 1-9 s&auml;testatud teenistussuhte peatumise aluseid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the bases for the termination of the service relationship provided for in clauses 108 1) -9) of this Act shall apply instead of the bases for the termination of an employment contract specified in subsection 6 (3); </inglise>
<eesti>2) paragrahvi 12 3. l&otilde;ike kohaldamisel asendatakse s&otilde;nad "t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine" s&otilde;nadega "teenistusest vabastamine"; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the application of subsection 12 (3), the words "termination of an employment contract" shall be replaced with the words "release from the service"; </inglise>
<eesti>3) paragrahvi 19 3. l&otilde;ikes osundatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumise aluste asemel kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punktides 1 - 6, 8 ja 9 s&auml;testatud teenistussuhte peatumise aluseid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the bases for the suspension of the service relationship provided for in clauses 108 1) -6), 8) and 9) of this Act shall apply instead of the bases for the suspension of an employment contract specified in subsection 19 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Sama s&auml;tte teise lause kohaldamisel asendatakse s&otilde;nad "p&auml;rast lepingu peatumist t&ouml;&ouml;le asuma" s&otilde;nadega "p&auml;rast teenistussuhte peatumist teenistusse asuma"; </eesti>
<inglise>In the application of the second sentence of the same provision, the words "started work after suspension of the contract" shall be replaced with the words "entered into the service after suspension of the service relationship"; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seaduse s&auml;tete kohaldamisel kuuluvad t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igused antud ametniku teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igust omavale isikule ja viimase poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud ulatuses teistele &uuml;lemustele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the application of provisions of the Employees Disciplinary Punishments Act, the rights of an employer shall rest with a person authorised to employ the given official in the service and with other superiors to the extent specified by the person with employment authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 88. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 88. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse kandmine teenistuslehele </eesti>
<inglise>Entry of disciplinary punishment into service record </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristus kantakse teenistuslehele. </eesti>
<inglise>A disciplinary punishment shall be entered in the service record. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse kustutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Cancellation of disciplinary punishment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kes m&auml;&auml;ras ametnikule distsiplinaarkaristuse, v&otilde;ib selle karistuse ennet&auml;htaegselt kustutada, kui ametnik ei ole toime pannud uut s&uuml;&uuml;tegu ja on n&auml;idanud end hea t&ouml;&ouml;tajana. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who or an administrative agency which imposes a disciplinary punishment on an official may cancel the punishment before the prescribed time, unless the official commits another offence, and if he or she proves to be a good employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarkaristuse ennet&auml;htaegne kustutamine vormistatakse kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele, kes distsiplinaarkaristuse kustutas, teise saab teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The cancellation of a disciplinary punishment before the prescribed time shall be made in writing in at least two copies of which one shall be retained by the person or administrative agency which cancels the disciplinary punishment and the other shall be given to the public servant. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse kustutamine kantakse teenistuslehele. </eesti>
<inglise>The cancellation of a disciplinary punishment shall be entered in the service record. </inglise>
