<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonid </eesti>
<inglise>Competition and Evaluation Committees </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 93. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 93. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnikke atesteerivad komisjonid </eesti>
<inglise>Committees for evaluation of officials </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikke atesteerivad j&auml;rgmised konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Competition and evaluation committees shall evaluate officials as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Riigikogu Kantselei ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - Riigikogu Kantselei ametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials of the Chancellery of the Riigikogu shall evaluate officials of the Chancellery of the Riigikogu; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.03.98 j&otilde;ust.25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.03.98 entered into force 25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </inglise>
<eesti>2) Vabariigi Presidendi Kantselei ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - Vabariigi Presidendi Kantselei ametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials of the Office of the President of the Republic shall evaluate officials of the Office of the President of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri Kantselei ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - &Otilde;iguskantsleri Kantselei ametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials of the Office of the Legal Chancellor shall evaluate officials of the Office of the Legal Chancellor; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Riigikantselei juures tegutsev k&otilde;rgemate riigiametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - ministeeriumide asekantslereid, Riigikantselei peadirektorit ja koordinatsioonidirektorit, ametite ja inspektsioonide peadirektoreid ja nende aset&auml;itjaid, maasekret&auml;re, ministeeriumide ja Riigikantselei osakondade direktoreid ja juhatajaid ning muude valitsusasutuste juhte, samuti ametnikke, keda kavatsetakse edutada m&otilde;nele nimetatud ametikohtadest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Higher State Public Servants at the State Chancellery shall evaluate deputy secretaries general of ministries, the director general and the director of co-ordination of the State Chancellery, directors general of executive agencies and inspectorates and their deputies, county secretaries, directors and heads of departments of ministries and the State Chancellery, heads of other government agencies, and officials who are to be promoted to any of these offices; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.03.98 j&otilde;ust.25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.03.98 entered into force 25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </inglise>
<eesti>5) valitsusasutuse ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - ministeeriumide, Riigikantselei, maavalitsuste, ametite, inspektsioonide ja muude valitsusasutuste ametnikke, keda ei ole loetletud k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 4, kusjuures ministeeriumi konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon atesteerib ministeeriumi valitsemisalas olevate valitsusasutuste osakondade juhatajaid ja nende kohalike t&auml;idesaatva riigiv&otilde;imu volitusi omavate asutuste juhte, samuti ametnikke, keda kavatsetakse edutada m&otilde;nele nimetatud ametikohtadest, ning Justiitsministeeriumi konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon atesteerib lisaks ka esimese ja teise astme kohtute ametnikke, samuti ametnikke, keda kavatsetakse edutada m&otilde;nele nimetatud ametikohtadest ning Riigikantselei ametnike konkursi ja atesteerimiskomisjon atesteerib maa-arhivaare, riigiarhivaari aset&auml;itjaid, eriarhiivide direktoreid ja Rahvusarhiivi osakonnajuhatajaid, samuti ametnikke, keda kavatsetakse edutada m&otilde;nele nimetatud ametikohtadest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a competition and evaluation committee of officials of a government agency shall evaluate officials of ministries, the State Chancellery, county governments, boards, inspectorates, and other government agencies who are not listed in clause 4) of this subsection; the competition and evaluation committee of a ministry shall evaluate the heads of departments of government agencies within the area of government of the ministry and heads of their regional offices with authority to exercise executive power, and officials who are to be promoted to any of these offices; the Competition and Evaluation Committee of the Ministry of Justice shall also evaluate officials of courts of first and second instance, and officials who are to be promoted to any of these offices; the Competition and Evaluation Committee of the State Chancellery shall evaluate county archivists, deputies of the State Archivist, directors of special archives and heads of departments of the National Archives, and officials who are to be promoted to any of these offices; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.03.98 j&otilde;ust.25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486; 25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.03.98 entered into force 25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486; 25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>6) Riigikontrolli ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - Riigikontrolli ja selle organite ametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials of the State Audit Office shall evaluate officials of the State Audit Office and its bodies; </inglise>
<eesti>7) vastava riigiametiasutuse ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - selle ametiasutuse ametnikke, keda ei ole loetletud k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1-6; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a competition and evaluation committee of officials of a particular state administrative agency shall evaluate officials of that administrative agency who are not set out in clauses 1) -6) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>8) valla v&otilde;i linna konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - selle valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste vanem- ja nooremametnikke; </eesti>
<inglise>8) a competition and evaluation committee of a rural municipality or a city shall evaluate junior and senior officials of the administrative agencies of this rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>8 (1)) maakondliku omavalitsusliidu juures tegutsev konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - selle maakonna valdade ja linnade ametiasutuste k&otilde;rgemaid (juhtide ja n&otilde;unike p&otilde;higruppidesse kuuluvaid) ametnikke ning maakondliku omavalitsusliidu b&uuml;roo ametnikke (v&auml;lja arvatud b&uuml;roo juhti); </eesti>
<inglise>8 (1)) a competition and evaluation committee at a local government association in a county shall evaluate the higher officials (who belong to the basic category of executive officers or advisers) of the administrative agencies in the rural municipalities and cities of this county and the officials of the bureau of the local government association in the county (except the head of the bureau); </inglise>
<eesti>8 (2)) &uuml;leriigilise omavalitsusliidu juures tegutsev konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - &uuml;leriigilise omavalitsusliidu b&uuml;roo ametnikke ja maakondlike omavalitsusliitude b&uuml;roode juhte; </eesti>
<inglise>8 (2)) a competition and evaluation committee at a national local government association shall evaluate the officials of the bureau of the national local government association and the heads of the bureaus of the local government associations in the counties; </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>9) Riigikantselei juures tegutsev ametnike reservi arvamist taotlevate isikute konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon - ametnikuna teenistuses mitteolevaid isikuid, kes taotlevad ametnike reservi arvamist. </eesti>
<inglise>9) the competition and evaluation committee at the State Chancellery for persons applying for assignment to the reserve of officials shall evaluate persons not employed in the service as officials who apply for assignment to the reserve of officials. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Komisjoni esimees v&otilde;ib erialasel v&otilde;i territoriaalsel p&otilde;him&otilde;ttel moodustada konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni spetsialiseeritud koosseise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The chairman of a committee may establish specialised memberships of the competition and evaluation committee on a professional or territorial basis. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 1-3 ja 6 nimetatud komisjonide esimehed v&otilde;ivad k&otilde;rgematest ametnikest juhtide atesteerimiseks moodustada komisjoni eraldi koosseise. </eesti>
<inglise>Chairmen of committees listed in clauses (1) 1) - 3) and 6) of this section may establish special memberships of the committee for evaluation of executive officers who are higher officials. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.03.98 j&otilde;ust.25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.03.98 entered into force 25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse ja konkursi korraldamise ja atesteerimise korra (sealhulgas iga-aastase vestluse korralduse) ning atesteerimisn&otilde;uded ametikohtade p&otilde;higruppidele kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The statutes of a competition and evaluation committee, the procedure for carrying out a competition and evaluation (including the organisation of the annual interview), and the evaluation requirements for the basic categories of offices shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664; 25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664; 25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 94. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 94. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni esimees </eesti>
<inglise>Chairman of committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigikogu Kantselei ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimeheks on kantselei direktor. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Chairman of the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials of the Chancellery of the Riigikogu shall be the Secretary General of the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 93 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 2, 3 ja 6 nimetatud konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonide esimeesteks on vastavalt Vabariigi Presidendi Kantselei direktori, &otilde;iguskantsleri ja riigikontrol&ouml;ri poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>The chairmen of competition and evaluation committees specified in clauses 93 (1) 2), 3) and 6) of this Act shall be persons appointed by the Director of the Office of the President of the Republic, the Legal Chancellor and the Auditor General, respectively. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.03.98 j&otilde;ust.25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.03.98 entered into force 25.04.98 - RT I 1998, 34, 486) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&otilde;rgemate riigiametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimeheks on riigisekret&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Chairman of the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Higher State Public Servants shall be the State Secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ministeeriumi ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimeheks on ministeeriumi kantsler v&otilde;i tema poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The chairman of the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials of a Ministry shall be the secretary general of a ministry or a person appointed by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigikantselei ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees on Riigikantselei peadirektor. </eesti>
<inglise>The Chairman of the Competition and Evaluation Committee of Officials at the State Chancellery shall be the director general of the State Chancellery. </inglise>
<eesti>Teiste k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes nimetamata valitsusasutuste konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonide esimeheks on vastava valitsusasutuse juht v&otilde;i tema poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>The chairmen of the competition and evaluation committees of other government agencies not listed in this subsection shall be the heads of the corresponding government agencies or persons appointed by them. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 93 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 7 nimetatud riigiametiasutuse ametnike konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimeheks on vastava ametiasutuse juht v&otilde;i tema poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The chairman of a competition and evaluation committee of officials of state agencies specified in clause 93 (1) 7) of this Act shall be the head of the corresponding administrative agency or a person appointed by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Valla v&otilde;i linna konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimehe m&auml;&auml;rab selle omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse volikogu, maakondliku omavalitsusliidu juures tegutseva konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimehe m&auml;&auml;rab maakondliku omavalitsusliidu liikmete &uuml;ldkoosolek, &uuml;leriigilise omavalitsusliidu juures tegutseva konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimeheks on &uuml;leriigilise omavalitsusliidu juhatuse esimees (juhataja). </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The chairman of a competition and evaluation committee of a rural municipality or a city shall be appointed by the local government council, the chairman of a competition and evaluation committee at a local government association in a county shall be appointed by the general meeting of the members of the local government association in the county, the chairman of a competition and evaluation committee at a national local government association shall be the chairman of the board (the head) of the national local government association. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees m&auml;&auml;rab komisjoni spetsialiseeritud koosseisu moodustamisel selle esimehe. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon the formation of a specialised membership of a competition and evaluation committee, the chairman of the committee shall appoint the chairman of the specialised membership. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Komisjoni esimees annab tema p&auml;devusse kuuluvate asjade otsustamisel k&auml;skkirju. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The chairman of a committee shall issue directives in deciding matters within his or her competence. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 95. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 95. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni liikmete m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of members of committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni liikmete arvu ja koosseisu m&auml;&auml;rab komisjoni esimees vastavalt vajadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The number of members and the membership of a competition and evaluation committee shall be specified by the chairman of the committee, as necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni peab kuuluma ametnikke, nende kutse- ja/v&otilde;i ameti&uuml;hingu(te) esindajaid ja s&otilde;ltumatuid asjatundjaid. </eesti>
<inglise>The committee shall include officials, representatives of their professional association(s) and/or trade union(s) and independent experts. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Komisjoni esimees m&auml;&auml;rab komisjoni koosseisust komisjoni aseesimehe, kes asendab esimeest tema &auml;raolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The chairman of a committee shall appoint from among the members of the committee a deputy chairman who shall substitute for the chairman in his or her absence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametnikku ei v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rata selle komisjoni liikmeks, kes peab teda atesteerima. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall not be appointed as a member of a committee which must evaluate him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigikantselei juures tegutseva ametnike reservi arvamist taotlevate isikute konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimehe ja liikmed m&auml;&auml;rab riigisekret&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The chairman and members of a competition and evaluation committee at the State Chancellery for persons applying for assignment to the reserve of officials shall be appointed by the State Secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (1)) Valla v&otilde;i linna konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni moodustab ja liikmed m&auml;&auml;rab valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu, komisjoni koosseisu peab kuuluma valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (1)) A competition and evaluation committee of a rural municipality or a city shall be formed and the members thereof shall be appointed by the rural municipality council or the city council, the membership of the committee shall include the rural municipality or city secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>Maakondliku omavalitsusliidu juures tegutseva konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni moodustab ja liikmed m&auml;&auml;rab maakondliku omavalitsusliidu liikmete &uuml;ldkoosolek, komisjoni koosseisu peavad kuuluma selle maakonna valdade ja linnade esindajad ja maasekret&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>A competition and evaluation committee at a local government association in a county shall be formed and the members thereof shall be appointed by the general meeting of the members of the local government association in the county, the membership of the committee shall include representatives of the rural municipalities and cities of this county and the county secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leriigilise omavalitsusliidu juures tegutseva konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni moodustab ja liikmed m&auml;&auml;rab &uuml;leriigilise omavalitsusliidu liikmete &uuml;ldkoosolek, komisjoni koosseisu peavad kuuluma maakondlike omavalitsusliitude esindajad ja Riigikantselei esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>A competition and evaluation committee at a national local government association shall be formed and the members thereof shall be appointed by the general meeting of the members of the national local government association, the membership of the committee shall include representatives of local government associations in counties and a representative of the State Chancellery. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni liikmed m&auml;&auml;rab komisjoni esimees allj&auml;rgnevas korras: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Members of a competition and evaluation committee shall be appointed by the chairman of the committee by the following procedure: </inglise>
<eesti>1) talle alluvaid ametnikke - omal valikul, l&auml;htudes ametnike erialasest asjatundlikkusest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) officials subordinate to him or her shall be appointed at the chairman's discretion, given the professional expertise of the officials; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&otilde;rgemalseisva ametiasutuse, ametnike kutse&uuml;hingu(te) ja/v&otilde;i ameti&uuml;hingu(te) ning &uuml;leriigiliste omavalitsusliitude esindajaid - vastava ametiasutuse, &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu ettepanekul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) representatives of a superior administrative agency, professional association(s) and/or trade union(s) of officials and national local government associations shall be appointed on the proposal of the corresponding administrative agency, union or association; </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>3) teadlasi ja s&otilde;ltumatuid asjatundjaid - kokkuleppel teadlase v&otilde;i asjatundjaga; </eesti>
<inglise>3) researchers and independent experts shall be appointed by agreement with the researcher or expert; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Riigikogu liikmeid - nende n&otilde;usolekul ja Riigikogu juhatuse teadmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) members of the Riigikogu shall be appointed with their consent and with the knowledge of the Board of the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>5) valdade ja linnade esindajaid - vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>5) representatives of rural municipalities and cities shall be appointed on the proposal of the corresponding rural municipality council or city council. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 96. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 96. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoniliikmete t&ouml;&ouml; tasustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration of members of committee </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni liikmete t&ouml;&ouml; tasustamise ja komisjoni liikmeks olekuga seotud l&auml;hetuste kulude h&uuml;vitamise tingimused, ulatus ja kord kehtestatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The conditions, extent and procedure for the remuneration of members of a competition and evaluation committee and for the reimbursement of business travel expenses of members of the committee shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;kord </eesti>
<inglise>Administration of Competition and Evaluation Committee </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 97. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 97. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni otsustusv&otilde;ime </eesti>
<inglise>Quorum of committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon v&otilde;i selle spetsialiseeritud koosseis on otsustusv&otilde;imeline, kui koosolekust v&otilde;tab osa vastavalt komisjoni v&otilde;i selle spetsialiseeritud koosseisu esimees, tema &auml;raolekul aseesimees ja v&auml;hemalt pooled liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A competition and evaluation committee or its specialised membership shall have a quorum if the chairman of the committee or of its specialised membership or, in his or her absence, the deputy chairman and at least one-half of the members participate in a meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Otsuse teeb komisjon v&otilde;i selle spetsialiseeritud koosseis koosolekust osav&otilde;tjate h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision shall be made by a committee or its specialised membership by a majority of participants in a meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;&auml;lte poolitumisel on otsustavaks esimehe h&auml;&auml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>If votes are equally divided, the vote of the chairman shall govern. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Otsus tehakse kolme p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates atesteerimise korraldamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A decision shall be made within three days after the date of evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 98. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 98. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimistulemuste vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of evaluation results </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Atesteerimistulemused vormistatakse konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsusena koosoleku protokollis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Evaluation results shall be documented as a decision of the competition and evaluation committee in the minutes of the meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametniku edutamisel toimuva atesteerimise ja perioodilise atesteerimise tulemused kantakse ametniku atesteerimisperioodi alguses avatud atesteerimislehele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Results of evaluation upon the promotion of an official and the results of regular evaluation shall be entered in the evaluation record of the official which is started at the beginning of evaluation period. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 99. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 99. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimise k&auml;ik </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation process </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Atesteerimisel kontrollitakse isiku vastavust ametikohale, hinnates tema t&ouml;&ouml;tulemusi ja vastavust ametikohal esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At an evaluation, the suitability of a person for a position shall be verified by assessing his or her work results and whether he or she meets the requirements set for his or her position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Atesteerimise viib l&auml;bi k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 93 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud vastav konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon, kes m&auml;&auml;rab ka atesteerimise viisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Evaluation shall be performed by the corresponding competition and evaluation committee specified in subsection 93 (1) of this Act which shall also determine the method of evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametikoha atesteerimisn&otilde;uded kinnitab riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuse juht koosk&otilde;lastatult vastava konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoniga, juhindudes Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud ametikohtade p&otilde;higruppide atesteerimisn&otilde;uetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The evaluation requirements for a position shall be approved by the head of a state or local government administrative agency in concordance with the corresponding competition and evaluation committee, taking guidance from the evaluation requirements established by the Government of the Republic for the basic categories of offices. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;tulemuste ja ametikohal esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele vastavuse hindamisel on aluseks ametniku vahetu &uuml;lemuse poolt ametniku atesteerimislehele iga-aastaste vestluste alusel kantud hinnangud ja nende p&otilde;hjal komisjonile esitatud ettepanekud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The basis for assessing the work results of an official and whether he or she meets the requirements set for the position shall be the assessments of the immediate superior of the official entered in the evaluation record of the official on the basis of the annual interviews and proposals made to the committee based on the assessments. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimisperioodi viimane vestlus peab toimuma hiljemalt kaks kuud enne perioodilist atesteerimist. </eesti>
<inglise>The last interview during an evaluation period shall take place not later than two months prior to a regular evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonil on &otilde;igus omal &auml;ran&auml;gemisel kontrollida ametniku vahetu &uuml;lemuse antud hinnangute paikapidavust, seejuures kuulub vahetu &uuml;lemuse negatiivne hinnang atesteerimisel kohustuslikule kontrollimisele. </eesti>
<inglise>A competition and evaluation committee has discretion to verify the validity of the assessments provided by the immediate superior of an official; a negative assessment from the immediate superior at an evaluation shall be subject to obligatory verification. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isiku t&ouml;&ouml;tulemusi ei hinda konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 91 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 4 ja 5 nimetatud juhtudel toimuval atesteerimisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) At an evaluation performed in the cases specified in clauses 91 (1) 4) and 5) of this Act, a competition and evaluation committee shall not assess the work results of a person. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 91 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 5 toimuval atesteerimisel l&auml;htutakse ametikohtade p&otilde;higruppide atesteerimisn&otilde;uetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An evaluation performed in the case specified in clause 91 (1) 5) of this Act shall be based on the evaluation requirements for the basic categories of offices. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 99 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 99 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsused </eesti>
<inglise>Decisions of competition and evaluation committees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku perioodilisel atesteerimisel v&otilde;ib konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon teha &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitu j&auml;rgmistest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon regular evaluation of an official, a competition and evaluation committee may make one or several of the following decisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lugeda ametnik atesteerituks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to declare the official suitable; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lugeda ametnik mitteatesteerituks ning teha ametiasutuse juhile ettepanek vabastada ametnik teenistusest v&otilde;i nimetada ta madalama p&otilde;higrupi v&otilde;i sama p&otilde;higrupi ametikohale, millel esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele ametnik on vastav; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to declare the official unsuitable and make a proposal to the head of the administrative agency to release the official from the service or to appoint him or her to a position in a lower basic category of offices or to a position in the same basic category of offices the requirements of which the official meets; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&uuml;kata atesteerimine kuni &uuml;heks aastaks edasi ja teha ametiasutuse juhile ettepanek ametniku koolitamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to postpone the evaluation for up to one year and make a proposal to the head of the administrative agency for training of the official; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teha ametiasutuse juhile ettepanek kohaldada ametnikule ergutust; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to make a proposal to the head of the administrative agency to apply an incentive in respect the official; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teha ametiasutuse juhile ettepanek ametniku edutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) make a proposal to the head of the administrative agency to promote the official. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 4 ja 5 nimetatud ettepanekud ei ole ametiasutuse juhile v&otilde;i ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omavale isikule kohustuslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>Proposals specified in clauses 4) and 5) of this subsection are not obligatory for the head of the administrative agency or the person with appointment authority. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 3 nimetatud otsust atesteerimise edasil&uuml;kkamise kohta v&otilde;ib sama ametniku suhtes rakendada &uuml;ks kord. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision concerning postponement of evaluation specified in clause 3) of this subsection may be applied once to each official. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud otsused peavad olema motiveeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>Decisions specified in clauses 2) and 3) of this subsection shall be reasoned. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 91 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 2 nimetatud juhul toimuval atesteerimisel otsustab konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon, kas ametnik on vastav v&otilde;i mittevastav ametikohale, kuhu ametnikku soovitakse edutada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon evaluation performed in the case specified in clause 91 (1) 2) of this Act, a competition and evaluation committee shall decide the suitability or unsuitability of an official for the position to which he or she is to be promoted. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku ametikohale mittevastavaks tunnistamise korral peab otsus olema motiveeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>A decision declaring an official unsuitable for a position shall be reasoned. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 91 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 5 nimetatud juhul toimuval atesteerimisel otsustatakse lugeda atesteeritav isik atesteerituks v&otilde;i mitteatesteerituks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon evaluation performed in the case specified in clause 91 (1) 5) of this Act, the person evaluated shall be declared suitable or unsuitable. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku mitteatesteerituks tunnistamise korral peab otsus olema motiveeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon declaring a person unsuitable, the decision shall be reasoned. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 91 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 4 nimetatud juhul toimuval atesteerimisel valib konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon kandideerivate isikute hulgast &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitu kandidaati, kes esitatakse ametikohale nimetamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon evaluation performed in the case specified in clause 91 (1) 4) of this Act, a competition and evaluation committee shall choose one or several candidates from among the persons applying for the position, to be presented for appointment to the position. </inglise>
<eesti>Mitme kandidaadi esitamise korral otsustab nimetamise isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on &otilde;igus nimetada ametnik ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>If several candidates are presented, the appointment shall be decided by the person or administrative agency with authority to appoint an official to the position. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 100. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 100. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimisleht </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation record </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Atesteerimisleht on riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuses ametniku kohta peetav dokument, millele kantakse ametniku ja tema vahetu &uuml;lemuse vahel katseaja l&otilde;pus toimuva ja iga-aastase vestluse tulemused, selle alusel antud vahetu &uuml;lemuse hinnang ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;tulemuste ja ametikohal esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele vastavuse kohta, atesteerimisperioodi viimasel vestlusel ka ametniku vahetu &uuml;lemuse poolt konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonile tehtavad ettepanekud, isiku atesteerimistulemused ning teised Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;ratud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An evaluation record is a document concerning an official which is maintained in a state or local government administrative agency and in which the results of the interview at the end of the probationary period and of the annual interviews between the official and his or her immediate superior, the assessment of the immediate superior, based on the interviews, of the work results of the official and whether he or she meets the requirements set for the position, and, upon the last interview during an evaluation period, the proposals made by the immediate superior of the official to the competition and evaluation committee, the evaluation results of the person and other information determined by the Government of the Republic are entered. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimislehe vormi ja t&auml;itmise juhendi kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The form of an evaluation record and instructions for its completion shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametniku atesteerimisleht avatakse atesteerimisperioodi alguses ja l&otilde;petatakse sellele atesteerimistulemuste kandmisega ning seda hoitakse koos isiku teenistuslehega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An evaluation record of an official shall be started at the beginning of an evaluation period and completed by entering evaluation results therein and it shall be maintained together with the service record of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud iga-aastase vestluse tulemusi, selle alusel antud hinnangut ning konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonile tehtavaid ettepanekuid tuleb iga kord ametnikule tutvustada kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates nende kandmisest atesteerimislehele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall, each time, be informed of the results of the annual interview, the assessment provided on the basis thereof and the proposals made to a competition and evaluation committee specified in subsection (1) of this section within three working days after they are entered in the evaluation record. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik, kes ei ole n&otilde;us vahetu &uuml;lemuse hinnangu ja ettepanekutega, v&otilde;ib kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mil vahetu &uuml;lemuse hinnang ja ettepanek sai v&otilde;i oleks pidanud saama talle teatavaks, esitada k&otilde;rgemalseisvale &uuml;lemusele eriarvamuse ja taotleda vahetu &uuml;lemuse otsustuse &otilde;igsuse kontrollimist. </eesti>
<inglise>An official who does not agree with the assessment and proposals of his or her immediate superior may, within two weeks after the date on which he or she was or should have been informed of the assessment and proposal of his or her immediate superior, submit a dissenting opinion to a higher ranking official and apply for a verification of the accuracy of the decision of the immediate superior. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametniku suhtes edutamisettepaneku tegemise ja ametniku perioodilise atesteerimise aja m&auml;&auml;ramise korral esitab selle ametiasutuse juht, kus ametnik on teenistuses, ametniku atesteerimislehe ametnikku atesteerivale konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjonile </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an official is presented for promotion and a date for regular evaluation of an official is specified, the head of the administrative agency in which the official is in service shall submit the evaluation record to the competition and evaluation committee evaluating the official. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 101. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 101. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimisn&otilde;uete tutvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Access to evaluation requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Atesteerimisn&otilde;uded peavad olema ametnikule tema teenistuskohas alati k&auml;ttesaadavad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Evaluation requirements shall always be accessible to an official in his or her place of service. </inglise>
<eesti>Edutamiseks esitatavale ametnikule teatab edutamisettepaneku tegija need n&otilde;uded hiljemalt edutamisettepaneku tegemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>An official presented for promotion shall be notified of these requirements by a person who proposes the promotion not later than on the date the promotion proposal is made. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;he aasta jooksul uute atesteerimisn&otilde;uete kinnitamisest v&otilde;ib ametnikke nende n&otilde;uete alusel atesteerida vaid ametniku n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Within one year after approval of new evaluation requirements, officials may be evaluated pursuant to these requirements only with the consent of the officials. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 102. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 102. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimise ajast, kohast ja viisist teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of date, place and method of evaluation </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimise ajast, kohast ja viisist teatab konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees atesteeritavale kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat enne atesteerimisp&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>The chairman of a competition and evaluation committee shall notify a person to be evaluated of the date, place and method of evaluation at least two weeks before the date of evaluation, in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 103. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 103. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimistulemustest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of evaluation results </inglise>
<eesti>(27.01.99 j&otilde;ust.28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.01.99 entered into force 28.02.99 - RT I 1999, 16, 276) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Atesteerimistulemustest teatab konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees atesteeritule kirjalikult hiljemalt otsuse tegemise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The chairman of a competition and evaluation committee shall notify the person evaluated of the evaluation results not later than on the working day following the date the decision is made, in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 91 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 1, 2 ja 4 nimetatud juhtudel teatab konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni esimees atesteerimistulemustest ametiasutuse juhile otsuse tegemisele j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval ning ametniku edutamise korral toimuval atesteerimisel ja perioodilise atesteerimise korral tagastab ametniku atesteerimislehe. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases specified in clauses 91 (1) 1), 2) and 4) of this Act, the chairman of a competition and evaluation committee shall notify the head of an administrative agency of the evaluation results on the working day following the making of the decision and, upon evaluation performed in the case of promoting an official or upon regular evaluation, shall return the evaluation record of the official. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 104. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 104. </inglise>
<eesti>Kordusatesteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Re-evaluation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik, kes ei ole n&otilde;us atesteerimistulemustega, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda kordusatesteerimist kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgnes p&auml;evale, mil ta sai v&otilde;i oleks pidanud saama teada atesteerimistulemustest, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 4. l&otilde;ikes loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who does not agree with the evaluation results may demand re-evaluation within two weeks after the day following the date he or she becomes aware or should have become aware of the evaluation results, except in the cases set out in subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kordusatesteerimise korraldab komisjon uues koosseisus &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates esialgse atesteerimise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Re-evaluation shall be conducted by the committee with a new membership within one month after the date of the initial evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kordusatesteerimise ajast, kohast ja viisist teatab komisjoni esimees atesteeritavale kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt n&auml;dal enne kordusatesteerimise p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The chairman of a committee shall notify a person to be evaluated of the date, place and method of evaluation at least one week before the date of re-evaluation, in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kordusatesteerimist ei saa n&otilde;uda: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Re-evaluation shall not be demanded if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui ametnikku atesteeriti edutamisettepaneku p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an official was evaluated on the basis of a proposal for promotion; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui ametnik ei ole n&otilde;us kordusatesteerimise tulemustega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an official does not agree with the re-evaluation results; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon hindas ametnikukandidaadi vastavust avaliku konkursi korras t&auml;idetavale ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a competition and evaluation committee evaluated the suitability of a candidate for a position to be filled by way of public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 105. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 105. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimise v&otilde;i kordusatesteerimise uue aja m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Specifying new evaluation or re-evaluation date </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Atesteerimise v&otilde;i kordusatesteerimise uus aeg m&auml;&auml;ratakse ametniku kirjaliku taotluse korral, kui ta ei saa ootamatult tekkinud takistuse t&otilde;ttu etten&auml;htud ajaks ilmuda konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni ning ametniku osalemist konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni koosolekul peab vajalikuks kas konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon v&otilde;i ametnik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A new evaluation or re-evaluation date shall be specified upon the written request of the official if he or she is unable to appear before a competition and evaluation committee at the prescribed time due to an unexpected hindrance and either the competition and evaluation committee or the official deem the participation of the official in the meeting of the competition and evaluation committee necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ametnik ei ole oma ilmumata j&auml;&auml;misest teatanud ega taotlenud atesteerimise uue aja m&auml;&auml;ramist hiljemalt konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni koosoleku toimumise ajaks, loeb komisjon ametniku m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta mitteilmunuks ning v&otilde;ib tema atesteerimise viia l&auml;bi ametniku osaluseta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an official has not given notice of failure to appear or requested for a new evaluation date to be specified by the date of the meeting of the competition and evaluation committee at the latest, the competition and evaluation committee shall deem the official to have not attended the evaluation, without good reason, and may evaluate him or her without the participation of the official. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui komisjon peab vajalikuks ametniku osalemist koosolekul, m&auml;&auml;rab komisjoni esimees kindlaks atesteerimise v&otilde;i kordusatesteerimise uue aja ning teeb selle teatavaks nii atesteeritavale kui ka ametiasutuse juhile, kes vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 92 1. l&otilde;ikele m&auml;&auml;ras kindlaks atesteerimise aja. </eesti>
<inglise>If the competition and evaluation committee deems the participation of the official in the meeting necessary, the chairman of the committee shall specify another date for evaluation or re-evaluation and shall notify both the person evaluated and the head of the administrative agency, who specified the evaluation date pursuant to subsection 92 (1) of this Act, thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 106. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 106. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku mitteatesteerituks tunnistamise tagaj&auml;rg </eesti>
<inglise>Consequence of declaring official to be unsuitable </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik, kelle suhtes konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjon on teinud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 99 (1) 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 2 nimetatud otsuse, vabastatakse ametist k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 117 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 2 alusel v&otilde;i nimetatakse tema n&otilde;usolekul madalama p&otilde;higrupi ametikohale kahe kuu jooksul, arvates konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsuse tegemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>A official concerning whom a competition and evaluation committee has made the decision specified in clause 99 (1) (1) 2) of this Act shall be released from office pursuant to clause 117 (1) 2) of this Act or appointed to a position in a lower basic category of offices with his or her consent within two months after the date the decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>Madalama p&otilde;higrupi ametikohale nimetatud ametnikke ei saa esitada edutamiseks &uuml;he aasta jooksul, arvates madalamale ametikohale ametisse astumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Officials appointed to a position in a lower basic category of offices shall not be presented for promotion within one year after the date of assuming office in a lower basic category of offices. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistussuhte peatumine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of Service Relationship of Official </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 107. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 107. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistussuhte peatumise m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of suspension of service relationship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku teenistussuhte peatumine t&auml;hendab ametniku ajutist vabanemist teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest ja ametiasutuse ajutist vabanemist kohustusest kindlustada ametnikule t&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Suspension of the service relationship of an official means a temporary release of the official from the performance of his or her functions and a temporary release of an administrative agency from the obligation to ensure employment to the official. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistussuhte peatumise ajaks s&auml;ilitatakse ametnikule seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel ja korras ametipalk koos lisatasudega v&otilde;i makstakse muud h&uuml;vitust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During the suspended period of the service relationship, an official shall retain his or her salary together with additional remuneration or shall be paid other compensation in the cases and pursuant to procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 108. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 108. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistussuhte peatumise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Grounds for suspension of service relationship </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistussuhe peatub: </eesti>
<inglise>A service relationship shall be suspended: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametniku kirjaliku avalduse alusel, kui teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igust omav isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus n&otilde;ustub teenistussuhte peatumisega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on the basis of a written application of an official if the person or administrative agency with employment authority consents to the suspension of the service relationship; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puhkuse ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the period of holiday; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the period of temporary incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ajaks, mil ametnik seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel t&auml;idab muid talle pandud riiklikke v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;lesandeid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) for the period when an official performs, in the cases provided by law, other state or local government functions assigned to him or her; </inglise>
<eesti>5) (Kehtetu - 29.12.98 j&otilde;ust.23.01.99, rakendatakse alates 01.12.98 - RT I 1999, 4, 54) </eesti>
<inglise>5) (Repealed - 29.12.98 entered into force 23.01.99, applies as of 01.12.98 - RT I 1999, 4, 54) </inglise>
<eesti>6) &otilde;ppekogunemise ajaks, samuti ajaks, mil reservv&auml;elane mobilisatsiooni t&otilde;ttu ei saa t&auml;ita oma ameti&uuml;lesandeid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) for the period of training exercises and for the period when a reservist is unable to perform his or her functions due to mobilisation; </inglise>
<eesti>7) ajaks, mil ametnikult ebaseaduslikult n&otilde;utakse &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmist teisel teenistuskohal ning ta keeldub niisuguste &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>7) for the period when an official is unlawfully required to perform functions in another position, and he or she refuses to perform such functions; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ajaks, mil ametnik on ametist k&otilde;rvaldatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 109 1. l&otilde;ike v&otilde;i paragrahv 110 1. l&otilde;ike alusel, samuti ajaks, mil ta on ametist k&otilde;rvaldatud m&otilde;nel muul seaduses s&auml;testatud alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>8) for the period when an official is excluded from office pursuant to subsection 109 (1) or subsection 110 (1) of this Act and for the period when he or she is excluded from office on some other grounds provided by law; </inglise>
<eesti>9) ajaks, mil ametnik on arestis v&otilde;i vahi all; </eesti>
<inglise>9) for the period when an official is under arrest or in custody; </inglise>
<eesti>10) muudel juhtudel, mil ametnik on seaduse v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel ajutiselt vabastatud teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>10) in other cases when an official is temporarily released from the performance of his or her functions pursuant to law or a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 109. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 109. </inglise>
<eesti>Joobes ametniku ametist k&otilde;rvaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Exclusion of intoxicated official from office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lemus k&otilde;rvaldab joobes ametniku selleks t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks ametist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A superior shall exclude an intoxicated official from office for that working day. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lemus on kohustatud ametist k&otilde;rvaldama ka joobe v&otilde;i arstimite j&auml;&auml;kn&auml;htudega v&otilde;i arstimite m&otilde;ju all oleva ametniku, kui t&ouml;&ouml; n&otilde;uab erilist t&auml;psust, on seotud suurema ohu allika valdamisega v&otilde;i selle vahetus l&auml;heduses t&ouml;&ouml;tamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>A superior is also required to exclude from office an official who shows signs of the residual effect of intoxication or medicines, or who is under the influence of medicines if the job demands particular accuracy, involves control over a major source of danger or working in its immediate vicinity. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti on &uuml;lemus kohustatud k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel ametnikku t&ouml;&ouml;le mitte lubama. </eesti>
<inglise>A superior is also required not to permit an official to work in the cases provided for in this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugune t&ouml;&ouml;le mittelubamine on v&otilde;rdsustatud ametist k&otilde;rvaldamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>Such prohibition to work is equal to exclusion from office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnikule ei maksta tasu aja eest, mil ta on ametist k&otilde;rvaldatud m&otilde;nel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall not be paid remuneration for the period he or she is excluded from office on any grounds provided for in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 110. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 110. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku ametist k&otilde;rvaldamine distsiplinaarasja menetluse ajaks </eesti>
<inglise>Exclusion of official from office for period of disciplinary procedure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igust omaval isikul on &otilde;igus k&otilde;rvaldada ametnik ametist distsiplinaarasja menetluse ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person with authority to impose a disciplinary punishment has the right to exclude an official from office for the period of disciplinary procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel ametist k&otilde;rvaldamise aja eest s&auml;ilitatakse ametnikule ametipalk koos k&otilde;igi etten&auml;htud lisatasudega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the period of exclusion from office pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, an official shall retain his or her salary together with all prescribed additional remuneration. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 111. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 111. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistussuhte peatumise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of suspension of service relationship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistussuhte peatumine vormistatakse k&auml;skkirja v&otilde;i korraldusega, v&auml;lja arvatud teenistussuhte peatumise korral k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 108 punktis 3 s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Suspension of a service relationship shall be made by way of a directive or order, except upon suspension of the service relationship on a basis provided for in clause 108 3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistussuhte peatumise kohta k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punktide 1 v&otilde;i 6 alusel tehakse kanne t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse, kui teenistussuhe peatub kauemaks kui kolmeks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An entry concerning suspension of the service relationship pursuant to clauses 10 1) or 6) of this Act shall be entered in the employment record book if the service relationship is suspended for longer than three months. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistusest vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release of Official from Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 112. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 112. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Authority to release from service </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku v&otilde;ib teenistusest vabastada isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>An official may be released from the service by a person or administrative agency authorised to employ him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 113. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 113. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistusest vabastamine teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release of official from service due to expiry of term of service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu vabastatakse teenistusest ametnik, kes oli ametisse nimetatud v&otilde;i valitud m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official appointed or elected to office for a specified period of time shall be released from the service due to the expiry of his or her term of service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ametniku teenistussuhe l&otilde;peb teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The service relationship of an official specified in subsection (1) of this section shall terminate on the day following the date of expiry of his or her term of service. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks ametisse nimetatud v&otilde;i valitud isikut ei vabastata, kui ta nimetatakse v&otilde;i valitakse samale ametikohale uueks t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person appointed or elected to office for a specified period of time shall not be released if he or she is appointed or elected to the same position for a new term. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 113 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 113 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Ministeeriumi kantsleri vabastamine ministri ja kantsleri koost&ouml;&ouml; mittelaabumise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release of secretary general of ministry due to failure of co-operation between minister and secretary general </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ministeeriumi kantsler vabastatakse teenistusest ministri hinnangul ministri ja kantsleri koost&ouml;&ouml; mittelaabumise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A secretary general of a ministry shall be released from service if, according to the minister, co-operation between the minister and the secretary general fails. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ministeeriumi kantslerit ei saa k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud alusel teenistusest vabastada enne aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumist ministri ja kantsleri koos t&ouml;&ouml;tamise algusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A secretary general of a ministry shall not be released from service on the basis specified in subsection (1) of this section earlier than one year after the minister and the secretary general commenced co-operation. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 114. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 114. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine ametniku algatusel </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service on initiative of official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik vabastatakse teenistusest tema enda algatusel kirjaliku avalduse alusel, mille ta on esitanud isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele, kellel on tema vabastamise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be released from the service on his or her own initiative on the basis of a written application which he or she submits to a person or administrative agency authorised to release him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik on kohustatud teenistusest lahkumisest ette teatama v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official is required to give at least one month's advance notice of his or her resignation from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui teenistusest lahkumise p&otilde;hjuseks on ametniku invaliidsus, haige v&otilde;i invaliidistunud perekonnaliikme hooldamise vajadus, siis on ametnik kohustatud lahkumisest ette teatama v&auml;hemalt viis kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>If the reason for resignation from the service is an official's disability or need to care for a sick or disabled family member, the official shall be required to give advance notice of at least five calendar days of his or her resignation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) Kokkuleppel isikuga, kellel on ametniku teenistusest vabastamise &otilde;igus, v&otilde;ib ametniku teenistusest lahkumise korral kohaldada l&uuml;hemat etteteatamist&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) In the case of resignation from service by an official, a shorter term for advance notice may be applied upon agreement with the person who is authorised to release the official from service. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistusest vabastamiseks esitatud avaldusest saab ametnik loobuda &uuml;ksnes tema vabastamise &otilde;igust omava isiku v&otilde;i ametiasutuse n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official may withdraw an application submitted for release from the service only with the consent of a person or administrative agency authorised to release him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel avalduses m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date specified in the application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 115. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 115. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine ametiasutuse likvideerimise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to winding-up of administrative agency </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik vabastatakse teenistusest ametiasutuse likvideerimise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be released from the service due to the winding-up of the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametiasutuse reorganiseerimine (&uuml;hendamine, liitmine, jagamine, eraldamine ja &uuml;mberkujundamine) ei ole ametniku vabastamise aluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Reorganisation of an administrative agency (merger, amalgamation, division, separation or alteration of legal form) shall not be a basis for the release of an official. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui reorganiseerimisega kaasneb ametikohtade koondamine, siis v&otilde;ib ametniku vabastada k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 116 1. l&otilde;ike alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>If a reorganisation results in lay-offs, an official may be released pursuant to &sect; 116 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametiasutuse alluvuse muutmine ei ole ametniku teenistusest vabastamise aluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A change in the subordination of an administrative agency shall not be a basis for the release of an official from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel ametiasutuse tegevuse l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date of termination of the activities of the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 116. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 116. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine koondamise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to lay-offs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku v&otilde;ib koondamise t&otilde;ttu teenistusest vabastada ametiasutuse koosseisus etten&auml;htud ametikohtade arvu v&auml;hendamisel, teenistuse &uuml;mberkorraldamisel v&otilde;i ebaseaduslikult teenistusest vabastatud ametniku teenistusse ennistamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official may be released from the service due to lay-offs if the number of positions on the staff of an administrative agency is reduced, if the service is restructured or if an unlawfully released official is reinstated in the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koondamisel on teenistusse j&auml;&auml;mise eelis&otilde;igus eelk&otilde;ige teenistujate esindajal, seej&auml;rel p&otilde;hikohaga ametnikel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of lay-offs, representatives of public servants have a preferential right to remain in the service, followed by officials on the regular staff. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hikohaga ametnikest on nimetatud &otilde;igus paremate teenistusalaste n&auml;itajatega ametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>Of the officials on the regular staff, an official with the best performance indicators has this right. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rdsete teenistusalaste n&auml;itajate korral eelistatakse ametnikku, kes on teenistuses saanud t&ouml;&ouml;vigastuse v&otilde;i kutsehaiguse, kellel on pikem teenistusstaa&zcaron; v&otilde;i kellel on &uuml;lalpeetavaid. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of equal performance indicators, an official who has suffered a work injury or contracted an occupational disease in the service, who has been employed in the service for a longer period or who has dependants shall be preferred. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametnikku ei vabastata, kui teda on v&otilde;imalik nimetada tema n&otilde;usolekul teisele ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall not be released if it is possible to appoint the official to another position with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondamise t&otilde;ttu vabanenud ametnik tuleb tema soovil kuue kuu jooksul, alates tema vabastamisest, teenistusse tagasi v&otilde;tta, kui tema teenistuskohas luuakse uusi v&otilde;i vabaneb olemasolevaid vabanenud ametniku kvalifikatsioonile vastavaid ametikohti. </eesti>
<inglise>An official who has been released due to a lay-off shall be re-employed in the service within six months as of the date on which he or she is released if the official so desires and if new positions are created in his or her place of service or existent positions which correspond to the qualifications of the released official are freed. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametikohtade arvu v&auml;henemisel on ametiasutuse juhil &otilde;igus teha ametnike &uuml;mberpaigutusi, vabastades koondamise t&otilde;ttu teenistusest isiku, kelle ametikoht s&auml;ilib, ning nimetada sellele ametikohale teise ametniku, kelle ametikoht koondatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the number of position s is reduced, the head of an administrative agency has the right to relocate officials, by releasing from the service, due to lay-offs, a person whose position is retained and appointing to this position another official whose position is redundant. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugune &uuml;mberpaigutamine on lubatud &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui &uuml;mberpaigutatava ametniku kvalifikatsioon ja teenistusalased n&auml;itajad on koondatava ametniku vastavate n&auml;itajatega v&otilde;rreldes paremad. </eesti>
<inglise>Such relocation shall be permitted only if the qualification and performance indicators of an official to be relocated are comparably better than the corresponding indicators of an official who is laid off. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel etteteatamist&auml;htajale (&sect; 130) j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An official shall be released from the service pursuant to subsection (1) of this section on the day following the deadline for advance notice of release (&sect; 130). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 117. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 117. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine ametikohale mittevastavuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to unsuitability for position </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku v&otilde;ib ametikohale mittevastavuse t&otilde;ttu teenistusest vabastada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official may be released from the service due to his or her unsuitability for the position: </inglise>
<eesti>1) katseaja ebarahuldavate tulemuste p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on the basis of unsatisfactory results of the probationary period, </inglise>
<eesti>2) atesteerimistulemuste p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) on the basis of evaluation results, </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui tal puudub dokument, mis on vastavas ametis t&ouml;&ouml;tamise kohustuslik tingimus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if he or she does not have a document which is a mandatory requirement for employment in a particular position, </inglise>
<eesti>4) ebapiisava keele- v&otilde;i suhtlemisoskuse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) due to inadequate language or communication skills, </inglise>
<eesti>5) kui tema tervislik seisund ei v&otilde;imalda p&uuml;sivalt oma teenistuskohustusi n&otilde;uetekohaselt t&auml;ita; </eesti>
<inglise>5) if his or her state of health does not allow the official to perform his or her duties continuously as required, </inglise>
<eesti>6) ebapiisavate t&ouml;&ouml;oskuste t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>6) due to inadequate professional skills. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Katseaja ebarahuldavate tulemuste p&otilde;hjal v&otilde;ib ametniku vabastada katseaja kestel, kaasa arvatud selle viimasel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official may be released during the probationary period, including on the last day thereof, on the basis of unsatisfactory results of the probationary period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Atesteerimistulemuste p&otilde;hjal vabastatakse ametnik kahe kuu jooksul, arvates konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsuse tegemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall be released on the basis of evaluation results within two months after the date a competition and evaluation committee makes its decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametis t&ouml;&ouml;tamise kohustuslikuks tingimuseks oleva dokumendi puudumise, ebapiisava keele- v&otilde;i suhtlemisoskuse v&otilde;i tervisliku seisundi t&otilde;ttu tuleb ametnik vabastada kohe p&auml;rast vastava asjaolu ilmnemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official shall be released due to the absence of a document which is a mandatory requirement for employment in the position, inadequate language or communication skills, or for health reasons immediately after the corresponding circumstance becomes known. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ametnik vabastatakse m&otilde;nel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 2-6 s&auml;testatud alusel, kui teda ei ole v&otilde;imalik tema n&otilde;usolekul nimetada teisele ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An official shall be released on any grounds provided for in clauses (1) 2) -6) of this section if it is impossible to appoint the official to another position with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastamise vormistamise dokumendis m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date specified in the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 118. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 118. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service for disciplinary offence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku v&otilde;ib teenistusest vabastada k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 84 s&auml;testatud distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official may be released from the service for a disciplinary offence provided for in &sect; 84 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistuskohustuste rikkumise (&sect; 84 p. 1) eest v&otilde;ib vabastada ametniku, kellel on kehtiv distsiplinaarkaristus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official with respect to whom a disciplinary punishment is in force may be released for a breach of his or her duties (clause 84 1)). </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuskohustuste j&auml;meda rikkumise, usalduse kaotamise (&sect; 84 p. 2) v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;ritu teo (&sect; 84 p. 3) eest v&otilde;ib ametniku vabastada ka siis, kui tal ei ole kehtivat distsiplinaarkaristust. </eesti>
<inglise>For a severe breach of duties, loss of confidence (clause 84 2)) or an indecent act (clause 84 3)), an official may also be released even if he or she has no disciplinary punishment in force. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel, arvates talle vabastamise vormistamise dokumendi teatavakstegemise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section on the day following the date he or she is notified of the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavoliliselt teenistusest lahkunud ametnik vabastatakse, arvates omavoliliselt teenistusest lahkumise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>An official who resigns from the service without authorisation shall be released on the day following the date of his or her unauthorised resignation from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 119. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 119. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to long-term incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku v&otilde;ib vabastada teenistusest, kui ta on haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse t&otilde;ttu teenistusest puudunud &uuml;le nelja kuu j&auml;rjest v&otilde;i &uuml;le viie kuu kalendriaasta jooksul, tuberkuloosi haigestumise t&otilde;ttu siis, kui ta on teenistusest puudunud &uuml;le kaheksa kuu j&auml;rjest v&otilde;i &uuml;le kaheksa kuu kalendriaasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official may be released from the service if he or she has been absent from the service due to illness or injury for more than four consecutive months or for more than five months within a calendar year, in the case of contracting tuberculosis, if he or she has been absent from the service for more than eight consecutive months or for more than eight months within a calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.11.07.96 - RT I 1996, 45, 850) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 11.07.96 - RT I 1996, 45, 850) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel v&otilde;ib ametniku vabastada ainult haiguslehel oleku ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official may only be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section during sick leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;vigastuse t&otilde;ttu ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks j&auml;&auml;nud ametniku teenistussuhe peatub ja talle s&auml;ilitatakse tema ametikoht kuni tervenemiseni v&otilde;i invaliidsuse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The service relationship of an official who is temporarily incapable for work due to a work injury shall be suspended, and the official's position shall be retained until his or her recovery or determination of his or her disability. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastamise vormistamise dokumendis m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date specified in the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 120. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 120. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine vanuse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to age </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku v&otilde;ib vabastada teenistusest vanuse t&otilde;ttu, kui ta on saanud 65-aastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official may be released from the service due to age when he or she attains sixty-five years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastamise vormistamise dokumendis m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date specified in the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 121. (Kehtetu - 24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 121. (Repealed - 24.10.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 122. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 122. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine ametniku ajateenistusse v&otilde;i asendusteenistusse kutsumise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to call-up for military service or alternate service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik vabastatakse teenistusest tema kutsumisel ajateenistusse v&otilde;i asendusteenistusse, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui teenistussuhe peatub k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punkti 1 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be released from the service if he or she is called up for military service or alternate service, except if the service relationship is suspended pursuant to clause 108 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel v&auml;hemalt kolm p&auml;eva enne kutsel m&auml;rgitud p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section at least three days before the date specified in the call-up notice. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 123. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 123. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisel </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service upon entry into force of conviction by court </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik vabastatakse teenistusest s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisel, millega talle m&otilde;isteti karistus tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest v&otilde;i karistus, mis v&auml;listab senise t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamise, arvates s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>An official shall be released from the service upon the entry into force of a conviction by a court by which he or she is sentenced to a punishment for an intentionally committed criminal offence or to a punishment which precludes continuation of the current employment as of the day following the date the conviction enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahi alla v&otilde;etud ametnik vabastatakse teenistusest p&auml;rast s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumist, arvates vahi alla v&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>An official taken into custody shall be released from the service after entry into force of a conviction by a court as of the date the official is taken into custody. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 124. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 124. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine teenistusse v&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service for violation of employment rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik vabastatakse teenistusest, kui tema ametisse nimetamisel v&otilde;i valimisel oli rikutud teenistusse v&otilde;tmise eeskirju. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be released from the service if employment rules are violated upon his or her appointment or election to office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnikku ei vabastata, kui vabastamist tingiv asjaolu on &auml;ra langenud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall not be released if a circumstance requiring release ceases to exist. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastamise vormistamise dokumendis m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date specified in the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 125. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 125. </inglise>
<eesti>L&auml;hedase sugulase v&otilde;i h&otilde;imlase teenistusest vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service of close relative by blood or marriage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusest vabastatakse &uuml;ks l&auml;hedases suguluses v&otilde;i h&otilde;imluses olevatest ametnikest, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad samas ametiasutuses ametikohtadel, millest &uuml;ks on teise vahetus alluvuses v&otilde;i teise poolt vahetult kontrollitav. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) One of two officials closely related by blood or marriage who hold positions in the same administrative agency of which one is in direct subordination of or immediately controlled by the other shall be released from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusse j&auml;&auml;mise eelis&otilde;igus on ametnikul k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 116 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>An official has a preferential right to remain in the service under the conditions provided for in subsection 116 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastamise vormistamise dokumendis m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall be released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the date specified in the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 126. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 126. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine ametniku valimisel Riigikogu liikmeks v&otilde;i Vabariigi Presidendiks </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service upon election of official as member of the Riigikogu or President of the Republic </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku valimisel Riigikogu liikmeks v&otilde;i Vabariigi Presidendiks vabastatakse ta ametist valimistulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the election of an official as a member of the Riigikogu or as President of the Republic, the official shall be released from office as of the date of announcement of the election results. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 127. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 127. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine teisele ametikohale asumisel muus ametiasutuses </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service upon assumption of another office in another administrative agency </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametist vabastatakse ametnik, kes nimetati v&otilde;i valiti riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse teenistuses teisele ametikohale muus ametiasutuses, v&auml;lja arvatud riigi osalusega ettev&otilde;tte juhtimis- v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorgani liikmeks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official in the state or local government service appointed or elected to another office in another administrative agency shall be released from office, except if he or she is appointed or elected as a member of the directing or supervisory body of an enterprise with state participation. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Ametniku asumisel uuele ametikohale muus ametiasutuses on nimetatud ametiasutus kohustatud aegsasti vormistama ametniku ametisse nimetamise ja sellest kohe teavitama ametiasutust, kus ametnik on antud hetkel teenistuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) If an official assumes a new office in another administrative agency, the specified administrative agency is required to formalise the appointment of the official to office in a timely manner and immediately notify the administrative agency where the official is in the service at a given moment thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik on kohustatud viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast valimistulemuste kinnitamist teavitama ametiasutust, kus ta on antud hetkel teenistuses, enda valimisest ametikohale muus riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuses. </eesti>
<inglise>An official is required to notify the administrative agency where he or she is in the service at the given moment of his or her election to an office in another state or local government administrative agency within five working days after the election results are approved. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel ametist hiljemalt kalendrip&auml;evast, mis vahetult eelneb teisele ametikohale asumiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud kalendrip&auml;evale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall be released from office pursuant to subsection (1) of this section not later than on the working day immediately preceding the date specified for assumption of another office. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastatud riigiametnik asub ametikohale, millele ta nimetati v&otilde;i valiti, siis teenistussuhe riigiga ei l&otilde;pe. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a state official released from the service pursuant to subsection (1) of this section assumes an office to which he or she is appointed or elected, the service relationship with the state shall not terminate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastatud kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnik asub sama kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutuses ametikohale, millele ta nimetati v&otilde;i valiti, siis teenistussuhe selle kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksusega ei l&otilde;pe. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a local government official released pursuant to subsection (1) of this section assumes the office to which he or she was appointed or elected in the same local government administrative agency, the service relationship with that local government shall not terminate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 128. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 128. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamine kodakondsuse muutumise t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Release from service due to change in citizenship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusest vabastatakse ametnik, kes lahkus Eesti kodakondsusest v&otilde;i oma vaba tahte alusel sai m&otilde;ne muu riigi kodakondsuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who renounces Estonian citizenship or becomes, of his or her free will, a citizen of another state shall be released from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik vabastatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel teenistusest vabastamise dokumendi vormistamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall be released from the service pursuant to subsection (1) of this section as of the day following the date of issuance of the document of release. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 129. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 129. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuse l&otilde;ppemine surma korral </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of service upon death </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku surma korral loetakse tema teenistus l&otilde;ppenuks surmap&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the death of an official, his or her service shall be deemed terminated as of the day following the date of his or her death. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 130. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 130. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamisest etteteatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Advance notice of release from service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiasutuse likvideerimise, ametniku koondamise, atesteerimise ebarahuldavate tulemuste v&otilde;i vanuse t&otilde;ttu teenistusest vabastamisest teatatakse ametnikule kirjalikult ette v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall be given at least one month's advance notice in writing of his or her release from the service due to the winding-up of an administrative agency, lay-off, unsatisfactory results of evaluation or age. </inglise>
<eesti>Pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu teenistusest vabastamisest teatatakse ametnikule kirjalikult ette v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>An official shall be given at least two weeks' advance notice in writing of release from the service due to his or her long-term incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Teenistujate esindaja teenistusest vabastamisest koondamise t&otilde;ttu teatatakse talle kirjalikult k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaegadest &uuml;ks kuu varem. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) A representative of public servants who is released from service due to lay-offs shall be notified of the release in writing one month before the commencement of the terms prescribed in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 1 (1). l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaega ei j&auml;rgita, makstakse ametnikule lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 131 s&auml;testatud h&uuml;vitusele palka iga etteteatamist&auml;htajast puudu j&auml;&auml;nud t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a term provided for in subsection (1) or (1 (1)) of this section is not observed, an official shall be paid, in addition to the compensation provided for in &sect; 131 of this Act, salary for each working day short of the term of notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 1 (1). l&otilde;ike kohaselt etteteatatud vabastamisest saab loobuda ainult ametniku kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Advance notice of release pursuant to subsection (1) or (1 (1)) of this section may be waived only with the written consent of an official. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;usolekust keeldumisel vabastatakse ametnik alusel, millest talle ette teatati, makstes k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 131 s&auml;testatud vastavat h&uuml;vitust. </eesti>
<inglise>If consent is refused, the official shall be released on the basis of which he or she was notified in advance and shall be paid the appropriate compensation provided for in &sect; 131 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 131. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 131. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitus teenistusest vabastamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation upon release from service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusest vabastamisel ametiasutuse likvideerimise v&otilde;i ametniku koondamise t&otilde;ttu makstakse ametnikule h&uuml;vitusena, kui ametnikul on avaliku teenistuse staa&zcaron;i (paragrahvid 153 - 156): </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon release from the service due to the winding-up of an administrative agency or lay-off, an official, if he or she has been employed in the public service (&sect;&sect; 153-156) for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alla kolme aasta - kahe kuu ametipalk; </eesti>
<inglise>1) less than 3 years, shall be paid his or her two months' salary as compensation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 3 - 5 aastat - kolme kuu ametipalk; </eesti>
<inglise>2) 3 - 5 years, shall be paid his or her three months' salary as compensation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 5 - 10 aastat - kuue kuu ametipalk; </eesti>
<inglise>3) 5 - 10 years, shall be paid his or her six months' salary as compensation; </inglise>
<eesti>(14.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.16.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 28, 167) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.03.2000 entered into force 16.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 28, 167) </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;le k&uuml;mne aasta - 12 kuu ametipalk. </eesti>
<inglise>4) more than 10 years, shall be paid his or her twelve months' salary as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Kui ametiasutuse likvideerimise v&otilde;i ametikoha koondamise t&otilde;ttu ametist vabastatud ametnik nimetatakse ametisse ametikohale, mida talle pakuti ametiasutuse likvideerimisel v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 116 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhul, enne ajavahemiku m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, mille eest talle vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikele h&uuml;vitist maksti, peab ta tagastama saadud h&uuml;vitise sellele ajavahemikule vastavas ulatuses, mille v&otilde;rra varem ta uuesti teenistusse asus, v&otilde;rreldes h&uuml;vitise maksmisel aluseks olnud ajavahemikuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) If an official released from office due to the winding-up of an administrative agency or due to lay-off is appointed to office to a position which he or she is offered upon winding-up of the administrative agency or in the case provided for in subsection 116 (1) of this Act before the period of time passes for which he or she is paid compensation pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, he or she shall return the received compensation to the extent corresponding to the period of time by which he or she is re-employed in the service earlier as compared to the period of time which is the basis upon payment of the compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistusest vabastamisel ametikohale mittevastava tervisliku seisundi, pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse, ajateenistusse v&otilde;i asendusteenistusse kutsumise t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i atesteerimistulemuste p&otilde;hjal makstakse ametnikule h&uuml;vitusena &uuml;he kuu ametipalk. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon release from the service for health reasons, due to a long-term incapacity for work, call-up for military or alternate service, or on the basis of evaluation results, an official shall be paid his or her one month's salary as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistusest vabastamisel vanuse v&otilde;i ametiasutuse s&uuml;&uuml;l teenistusse v&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumise t&otilde;ttu makstakse ametnikule h&uuml;vitusena kolme kuu ametipalk. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon release from the service due to age or a violation of employment rules by the fault of an administrative agency, an official shall be paid his or her three months' salary as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ministeeriumi kantsleri teenistusest vabastamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 113 (1) 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud alusel makstakse talle h&uuml;vitusena ametipalk ametiaja l&otilde;puni j&auml;&auml;vate kuude eest, kuid mitte rohkem kui kuue kuu ametipalk. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon release from the service of a secretary general of a ministry on the basis provided for in subsection 113 (1) (1) of this Act, he or she shall be paid his or her salary for the months which remain until the end of the term of office as compensation, but not more than six months' salary. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 132. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 132. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of release from service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusest vabastamine vormistatakse k&auml;skkirja v&otilde;i korraldusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Release from the service shall be made by way of a directive or order. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigikogu v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu vormistab vabastamise otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The Riigikogu or a local government council shall release by way of a resolution. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vabastamise k&auml;skkiri, korraldus v&otilde;i otsus peab vastama haldusdokumentidele esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele ja sisaldama v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A directive, order or resolution for release must comply with requirements set for administrative documents and shall contain at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametiasutuse nimetust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the administrative agency; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ametniku ees- ja perekonnanime; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the given name and surname of the official; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametikoha nimetust, millelt ametnik vabastatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the title of the position from which the official is released; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vabastamise aluse formuleeringut viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the basis for release with reference to the section, subsection or clause of the applicable Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ametnikule makstava h&uuml;vituse suurust, kui vabastamisega kaasneb h&uuml;vituse maksmine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the amount of compensation to be paid to the official if release from the service brings about the payment of compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest vabastamisel kantakse vabastamise vormistamise dokumenti ka t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seaduse paragrahv 11 2. l&otilde;ikes loetletud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon release from the service for a disciplinary offence, the document of release shall also include information set out in subsection 11(2) of the Employees Disciplinary Punishments Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teenistusest vabastamise kohta tehakse ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse kanne, milles m&auml;rgitakse vabastamise kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An entry concerning release from the service shall be made in the employment record book of an official, indicating the date of release. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamise aluse formuleeringu viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile kannab ametiasutus ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse ainult ametniku n&otilde;udel. </eesti>
<inglise>The basis for release from the service with reference to the section, subsection and clause of the applicable Act shall be entered by an administrative agency in the employment record book of an official only on the demand of the official. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 133. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 133. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusest vabastamise aja piirang </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on timing of release from service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikku ei v&otilde;i koondamise, ametis t&ouml;&ouml;tamise kohustuslikuks tingimuseks oleva dokumendi puudumise v&otilde;i vanuse t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i atesteerimistulemuste p&otilde;hjal teenistusest vabastada ajal, mil teenistussuhe on peatunud m&otilde;nel k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punktides 2-10 s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall not be released from the service due to lay-off, the absence of a document which is a mandatory requirement for employment in the position, age or on the basis of evaluation results during the time the service relationship is suspended on any grounds provided for in clauses 108 2) -10) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnikku tema raseduse ajal, samuti naist, kes kasvatab alla kolmeaastast last, ei v&otilde;i teenistusest vabastada koondamise, pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i tervisliku seisundi mittevastavuse t&otilde;ttu, samuti atesteerimistulemuste p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official who is pregnant or a woman raising a child under three years of age shall not be released from the service due to lay-off, a long-term incapacity for work, health reasons or on the basis of evaluation results. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametniku, kes on seaduse v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korras valitud teenistujaid esindavasse organisatsiooni v&otilde;i teenistujaid esindavaks isikuks, v&otilde;ib vabastada teenistusest koondamise, ebapiisava keele- v&otilde;i suhtlemisoskuse, mittevastava terviseseisundi, vanuse v&otilde;i teenistusse v&otilde;tmise eeskirjade rikkumise, distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepanemise t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i atesteerimistulemuste p&otilde;hjal tema esindajaks olemise ajal ja &uuml;he aasta jooksul p&auml;rast seda ainult ametiasutuse asukoha t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official elected, pursuant to the procedure established by law or a regulation of the Government of the Republic, to an organisation representing public servants or as a representative of public servants may be released from the service due to lay-off, inadequate language or communication skills, health reasons, age, a violation of employment rules, commission of a disciplinary offence or on the basis of evaluation results at the time he or she acts as a representative and within one year thereafter only with the consent of the labour inspector of the location of the administrative agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor peab kirjalikult p&otilde;hjendama teenistujate esindaja teenistusest vabastamiseks n&otilde;usoleku andmist v&otilde;i sellest keeldumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A labour inspector shall justify in writing the reasons for granting or refusing to grant consent to the release of a representative of public servants from service. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne vastava otsuse tegemist peab t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor p&ouml;&ouml;rduma kirjalikult teenistujaid esindava organisatsiooni poole arvamuse saamiseks teenistujate esindaja vabastamise kohta, kui see esindaja on valitud teenistujaid esindava organisatsiooni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>Before making the corresponding decision, the labour inspector shall submit a written request to an organisation representing public servants in order to obtain an opinion concerning the release of the representative of the public servants from service, if such representative has been elected by the organisation representing public servants. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistujaid esindav organisatsioon annab oma kirjaliku arvamuse &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The organisation representing public servants shall provide a written opinion within one week as of the date of the request. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Keelatud on teenistujate esindaja teenistusest vabastamine tulenevalt tema seaduslikust tegevusest teenistujate huvide esindamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) It is prohibited to release a representative of public servants from service as a result of his or her lawful activities in representing the interests of the public servants. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ebaseadusliku tegevuse peale saab esitada kaebuse halduskohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A complaint against the unlawful activities of a labour inspector may be submitted to an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.2000 entered into force 07.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 144) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 134. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 134. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;raamatu andmine ja l&otilde;pparve maksmine teenistusest vabastamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Return of employment record book and payment of final settlement upon release from service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiasutus on kohustatud andma ametnikule t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu ja maksma l&otilde;pparve teenistusest vabastamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An administrative agency is required to return the employment record book and pay the final settlement to an official on the day of release from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui teenistusest vabastamise p&auml;eval j&auml;i t&ouml;&ouml;raamat ametnikule andmata v&otilde;i l&otilde;pparve maksmata, on ametiasutus kohustatud andma ametnikule t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu vastava n&otilde;ude esitamise p&auml;eval ja maksma l&otilde;pparve viie kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates n&otilde;ude esitamisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the employment record book is not returned and the final settlement is not paid to an official on the day of release from the service, the administrative agency is required to return the employment record book to the official on the day such claim is made and to pay the final settlement within five calendar days after the day following the submission of the claim. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu andmisega viivitati ametiasutuse s&uuml;&uuml;l, on ametiasutus kohustatud vabastatud ametnikule maksma ametipalka t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu andmisega viivitatud iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If return of the employment record book is delayed by the fault of an administrative agency, the administrative agency is required to pay the released official a salary for each working day by which return of the employment record book is delayed. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;pparve t&auml;htaegse maksmata j&auml;tmise korral on ametiasutus kohustatud maksma ametipalka l&otilde;pparve v&auml;ljamaksmisega viivitatud iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva eest, kuid mitte &uuml;le ametniku &uuml;he kuu ametipalga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon failure to pay the final settlement by the due date, the administrative agency is required to pay a salary for each working day by which the payment of the final settlement is delayed but not more than the official's one month's salary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 135. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 135. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ude&otilde;igus ebaseaduslikult teenistusest vabastamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Right of claim upon unlawful release from service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ebaseaduslikult teenistusest vabastatud ametnikul on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda vabastamise seadusevastaseks tunnistamist, teenistusest vabastamise aluse muutmist ja tasu teenistusest sunnitult puudutud aja eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who is unlawfully released from the service has the right to demand that his or her release from the service be declared unlawful and to demand amendment of the basis for the release and remuneration for the period of forced absence from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ametnik loobub ennistamisest, on ametiasutus kohustatud maksma talle h&uuml;vitusena kuue kuu ametipalga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an official waives reinstatement, the administrative agency is required to pay the official six months' salary as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnike reserv </eesti>
<inglise>Reserve of Officials </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldeeskirjad </eesti>
<inglise>General Rules </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 136. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 136. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnike reservi eesm&auml;rgid </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of reserve of officials </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnike reservi eesm&auml;rkideks on kindlustada: </eesti>
<inglise>The purpose of the reserve of officials is to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutustel ametnikukandidaatide leidmine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) state and local government administrative agencies find candidates for officials; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenistuses mitteolevale konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni otsuse alusel reservi arvatud isikule teenistuse leidmine riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikuna; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who is not in the service and who is assigned to the reserve of officials on the basis of the decision of a competition and evaluation committee finds employment as a state or local government official; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ametikohalt vabastatud isikule uuesti teenistuse leidmine riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikuna. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person released from his or her position finds new employment as a state or local government official. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 137. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 137. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatud ametnike arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of officials assigned to reserve </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnike reservi arvestust peetakse Riigikantseleis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The State Chancellery shall maintain a register of officials in the reserve. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reservis hoitakse reservi arvatud ametnike nimekirja ja teenistuslehti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The list and service records of officials assigned to the reserve shall be maintained in the reserve. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvamine </eesti>
<inglise>Assignment to Reserve </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 138. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 138. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatavad isikud </eesti>
<inglise>Persons assigned to reserve </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall be assigned to the reserve: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise, ametiasutuse likvideerimise, ametniku koondamise, pikaajalise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i tervisliku seisundi mittevastavuse t&otilde;ttu ametikohalt vabastatud ametnik v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis l39 loetletud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an official released from his or her position due to the expiry of his or her term of service, winding-up of an administrative agency, lay-off, long-term incapacity for work or health reasons, except in the cases set out in &sect; 139 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Riigikantselei juures tegutseva ametnike reservi arvamist taotlevate isikute konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni poolt atesteerituks loetud isikud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons declared suitable by the competition and evaluation committee at the State Chancellery for persons applying for assignment to the reserve of officials; </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>3) konkursi- ja atesteerimiskomisjoni poolt ametikohale nimetamiseks esitatud ametnikuna teenistuses mitteolev isik, kes j&auml;i temast s&otilde;ltumatutel p&otilde;hjustel ametikohale nimetamata. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person who is not employed in the service as official and who is presented for appointment to a position by a competition and evaluation committee but who is not appointed to the position for reasons independent of him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664; 25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664; 25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 139. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 139. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikud, keda reservi ei arvata </eesti>
<inglise>Persons not assigned to reserve </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi ei arvata: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall not be assigned to the reserve: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametnikku, kes teenistusest vabastamisel ei soovi reservi arvamist, kuigi tal k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 138 alusel on selleks &otilde;igus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an official who, upon release from the service, does not desire assignment to the reserve although he or she has this right pursuant to &sect; 138 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikut, kes on teenistusest vabastatud teenistust&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise t&otilde;ttu, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui ta enne antud ametisse nimetamist t&ouml;&ouml;tas m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks teenistusse v&otilde;etud riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikuna; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who is released from the service due to the expiry of his or her term of service, except if he or she worked as a state or local government official employed in the service for an unspecified period of time before appointment to that particular office; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&auml;ielikult t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) persons with total incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 140. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 140. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of assignment to reserve </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistusest vabastamisel saadetakse viivitamatult ametniku teenistusleht ja selle juurde kuuluvate dokumentide &auml;rakirjad Riigikantseleile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon release from the service, the service record of an official and copies of accompanying documents shall be promptly sent to the State Chancellery. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui vabastatud ametnik soovib reservi arvamist, lisatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud dokumentidele tema avaldus reservi arvamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a released official desires assignment to the reserve, his or her application for assignment to the reserve shall be appended to the documents specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reservi arvamine vormistatakse riigisekret&auml;ri k&auml;skkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Assignment to the reserve shall be made by way of a directive of the State Secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatud isiku &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and Obligations of Person Assigned to Reserve </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 141. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 141. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservis oleku aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Reserve period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reservi arvatud isik on reservi nimekirjas kuni ametikohale nimetamiseni v&otilde;i reservist k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 150 alusel v&auml;ljaarvamiseni, kuid mitte kauem kui kuus kuud j&auml;rjest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person assigned to the reserve shall be on the reserve list until appointment to office or removal from the reserve pursuant to &sect; 150 of this Act, but for not longer than six consecutive months. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel v&otilde;ib reservi arvatud isiku reservis oleku aega pikendada igal kuul tema poolt esitatud sooviavalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon expiry of the term established in subsection (1) of this section, the reserve period of a person assigned to the reserve may be extended each month on the basis of his or her request. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 142. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 142. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ta j&auml;&auml;nud ametniku registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of official left without work </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;ta j&auml;&auml;nud ametnik, kaasa arvatud reservi arvatu, registreerib end t&ouml;&ouml;tu abiraha ning t&auml;iend- ja &uuml;mber&otilde;ppe stipendiumi saamiseks elukohaj&auml;rgses t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who is left without work, including a person assigned to the reserve, shall register himself or herself for receipt of unemployment benefits and a stipend for in-service training and re-training at the employment office of his or her residence. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatut t&auml;iend- v&otilde;i &uuml;mber&otilde;ppele saates arvestatakse atesteerimiskomisjoni sellekohast soovitust. </eesti>
<inglise>The recommendation of an evaluation committee shall be considered when sending an official assigned to the reserve for in-service training or re-training. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 143. (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 143. (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 144. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 144. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatu kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of person assigned to reserve </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reservi arvatud isik on kohustatud l&auml;bi tegema talle pakutud t&auml;iend- v&otilde;i &uuml;mber&otilde;ppe v&otilde;i atesteerimise. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person assigned to the reserve is required to undergo in-service training or re-training offered to him or her, or evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik, kes m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta keeldus t&auml;iend- v&otilde;i &uuml;mber&otilde;ppest v&otilde;i atesteerimisest, arvatakse reservist v&auml;lja k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 150 punkti 6 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who, without good reason, refuses in-service training, re-training or evaluation shall be removed from the reserve pursuant to clause 150 6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 145. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 145. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatu staa&zcaron; </eesti>
<inglise>Length of service of person assigned to reserve </inglise>
<eesti>Reservis viibimise aeg arvatakse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvidele 153-156 avaliku teenistuse staa&zcaron;i hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>The reserve period shall be included in the length of the public service pursuant to &sect;&sect; 153-156 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 146. (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 146. (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist ametikohale nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment to Office from Reserve </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 147. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 147. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist ametisse nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment to office from reserve </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikku vajava ametiasutuse juht teatab vabast ametikohast riigisekret&auml;rile, m&auml;rkides &auml;ra t&auml;idetava ametikoha nimetuse ja selle t&auml;itmiseks esitatavad n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of an administrative agency seeking an official shall notify the State Secretary of a vacant position, indicating the title of the position to be filled and the requirements set for that position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigisekret&auml;r saadab ametnikku vajava ametiasutuse juhile kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates taotluse saamise p&auml;evast, v&auml;ljav&otilde;tte reservi nimekirjast nende isikute kohta, kes vastavad esitatud n&otilde;uetele, samuti &auml;rakirja nende teenistuslehest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The State Secretary shall, within three working days after receipt of a request, send an extract from the reserve list with respect to those persons who meet the set requirements and copies of their service records to the head of an administrative agency seeking an official. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametniku valikul reservi nimekirjast tehtud v&auml;ljav&otilde;tte j&auml;rgi ei ole ametiasutuse juht seotud isikute reservi arvamise j&auml;rjekorraga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) When selecting an official according to an extract made from a reserve list, the head of an administrative agency shall not be bound by the sequence in which persons were assigned to the reserve. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sobiva kandidaadi nimetab ametiasutuse juht ametikohale isiku avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The head of an administrative agency shall appoint a suitable candidate to office on the basis of an application by the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&auml;rast ametniku ametisse astumist taotleb ametiasutuse juht Riigikantseleilt ametniku teenistuslehe ja selle juurde kuuluvad dokumendid, mis saadetakse ametiasutuse juhile viivitamatult p&auml;rast tema taotluse Riigikantseleile j&otilde;udmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) After an official has assumed office, the head of an administrative agency shall request the official's service record and its accompanying documents from the State Chancellery which shall be sent to the head of the administrative agency promptly after receipt of his or her request by the State Chancellery. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 148. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 148. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatud isiku nimetamine asendajaks v&otilde;i kohuset&auml;itjaks </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of person assigned to reserve as substitute or acting official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reservi arvatud isiku v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta teenistusse ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku asendajana v&otilde;i puuduva ametniku kohuset&auml;itjana. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person assigned to the reserve may be employed in the service as a substitute for a temporarily absent official or as a person acting in the capacity of an absent official. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ajutiselt &auml;raoleva ametniku asendajana v&otilde;i puuduva ametniku kohuset&auml;itjana reservist teenistusse v&otilde;etud isik j&auml;&auml;b reservi nimekirja ning tal on asendajaks v&otilde;i kohuset&auml;itjaks olemise ajal k&otilde;ik reservi arvatud isiku &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person employed in the service from the reserve as a substitute for a temporarily absent official or as a person acting in the capacity of an absent official shall remain on the reserve list and, during the period the person acts as a substitute or acting official, he or she shall have all the rights granted to a person assigned to the reserve. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 149. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 149. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatu &otilde;igus keelduda ametisse nimetamisest </eesti>
<inglise>Right of person assigned to reserve to refuse appointment to office </inglise>
<eesti>Reservi arvatud isik v&otilde;ib ametisse nimetamisest keelduda, kui pakutav ametikoht: </eesti>
<inglise>A person assigned to the reserve may refuse appointment to office if the position offered: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei vasta tema tervislikule seisundile; </eesti>
<inglise>1) is not suitable to the person's state of health; </inglise>
<eesti>2) eeldab k&otilde;rgemat kvalifikatsiooni v&otilde;i teistsugust erialast ettevalmistust kui see, mis on antud ametnikul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) requires a higher qualification or different professional training than the given official has; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei v&otilde;imalda kasutada laste kasvatamiseks etten&auml;htud soodustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) does not enable the person to use benefits prescribed for the raising of children; </inglise>
<eesti>4) asub teises paikkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise>4) is located in another locality. </inglise>
<eesti>5. jagu. </eesti>
<inglise>Division 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist v&auml;ljaarvamine </eesti>
<inglise>Removal from Reserve </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 150. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 150. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist v&auml;ljaarvamise aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Timing of removal from reserve </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist arvatakse v&auml;lja: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall be removed from the reserve: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isik, kes nimetati ametikohale, v&auml;lja arvatud asendaja v&otilde;i kohuset&auml;itjana - arvates ametikohale nimetamise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person who is appointed to office, except as a substitute or acting official, as of the date of appointment to office; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isik, kes keeldus vastu v&otilde;tmast kahte pakutud ametikohta - arvates teise keeldumise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 149 loetletud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person who refuses to accept two positions offered, as of the day following the date of second refusal, except in the cases set out in &sect; 149 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isik, kes lahkus Eesti kodakondsusest v&otilde;i oma vaba tahte alusel sai m&otilde;ne muu riigi kodakondsuse - arvates reservist v&auml;ljaarvamise otsuse tegemise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person who renounces Estonian citizenship or, of his or her free will, becomes a citizen of another state, as of the date of the decision concerning removal from the reserve; </inglise>
<eesti>4) isik, kes esitas avalduse reservist v&auml;ljaarvamiseks - arvates avalduses m&auml;rgitud p&auml;evast, kuid mitte hiljem kui &uuml;he n&auml;dala p&auml;rast avalduse esitamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person who submits an application for removal from the reserve, as of the date specified in the application, but not later than one week after the day following the date of submission of the application; </inglise>
<eesti>5) reservis viibimise aja jooksul ametisse nimetamata isik - k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 141 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a person who is not appointed to office during the reserve period, upon expiry of the term provided for in &sect; 141 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) isik, kes m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta keeldus t&auml;iend- v&otilde;i &uuml;mber&otilde;ppest v&otilde;i atesteerimisest - arvates keeldumisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a person who refuses to undergo in-service training, re-training or evaluation, without good reason, as of the day following the refusal; </inglise>
<eesti>7) isik, kes suri reservis viibimise ajal - arvates surmap&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a person who dies during the reserve period, as of the day following the date of death, </inglise>
<eesti>8) I grupi invaliid - arvates invaliidsuse m&auml;&auml;ramise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>8) a Category I disabled person, as of the date of designation of his or her disability. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 151. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 151. </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist v&auml;ljaarvamise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalities of removal from reserve </inglise>
<eesti>Reservist v&auml;ljaarvamine vormistatakse riigisekret&auml;ri k&auml;skkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>Removal from the reserve shall be made by way of a directive of the State Secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 152. (Kehtetu - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 152. (Repealed - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron; </eesti>
<inglise>Length of Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 153. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 153. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron;i arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of length of service </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron;i hulka arvatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>Length of service shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Riigikogu liikme, Vabariigi Presidendi, Vabariigi Valitsuse liikme ja kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu liikme volituste aeg, samuti teenistuse aeg Eesti riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutustes ametniku, abiteenistuja v&otilde;i koosseisuv&auml;lise teenistujana; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the term of authority of a member of the Riigikogu, the President of the Republic, a member of the Government of the Republic and a member of a local government council, and a period of service in state or local government administrative agencies of Estonia as an official, a member of support staff or a non-staff public servant; </inglise>
<eesti>(14.04.98 j&otilde;ust.08.05.98 - RT I 1998, 38, 563) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.04.98 entered into force 08.05.98 - RT I 1998, 38, 563) </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenistuses mitteolevatel isikutel reservis viibimise aeg, kuid mitte rohkem kui kuus kuud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for persons who are not in service, a period of being in the reserve, but not more than six months; </inglise>
<eesti>(25.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.11.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 110, 1809) </inglise>
<eesti>3) teenistuse aeg Eesti kaitsev&auml;es ja piirivalves, samuti asendusteenistuse aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a period of service in the Armed Forces or the Border Guard of Estonia, and a period of alternate service; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &otilde;pingute aeg, kui isiku suunas &otilde;ppima Eesti riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametiasutus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a period of study if a person was sent to study by a state or local government administrative agency of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>5) (v&auml;lja j&auml;etud - 20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>5) (omitted - 20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 154. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 154. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron;i katkemine </eesti>
<inglise>Interruption of length of service </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron; katkeb, kui isik vabastati teenistusest v&otilde;i reservist kuriteo v&otilde;i distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo toimepanemise v&otilde;i Eesti kodakondsusest lahkumise v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne muu riigi kodakondsuse saamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>Length of service shall be interrupted if a person is released from the service or reserve due to committing a criminal or disciplinary offence, renouncing Estonian citizenship or becoming a citizen of another state. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 155. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 155. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron;i t&otilde;endamine </eesti>
<inglise>Certification of length of service </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusstaa&zcaron;i t&otilde;endatakse kandega t&ouml;&ouml;raamatus, samuti ametiasutuse v&otilde;i arhviiviasutuse poolt n&otilde;uetekohaselt vormistatud muude dokumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise>Length of service shall be certified by an entry in the employment record book and by other documents issued by an administrative agency or archive in accordance with requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 156. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 156. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;ruste andmise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to issue regulations of the Government of the Republic </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsusel on &otilde;igus anda m&auml;&auml;rusi k&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic has the right to issue regulations for the implementation of the provisions of this Chapter. </inglise>
<eesti>12. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 12 </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusleht ja t&ouml;&ouml;raamat </eesti>
<inglise>Service Record and Employment Record Book </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 157. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 157. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistusleht </eesti>
<inglise>Service record of official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametniku kohta peetakse teenistuslehte, millele m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A service record shall be maintained concerning an official which shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name, surname and personal identification code; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&uuml;nniaeg ja -koht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date and place of birth; </inglise>
<eesti>3) perekonnaseis; </eesti>
<inglise>3) marital status; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haridus ja eriala; </eesti>
<inglise>4) education and area of specialisation; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ametivande andmise kuup&auml;ev ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the date and place of taking the oath of office; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teenistusk&auml;ik, sealhulgas teenistusest vabastamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile; </eesti>
<inglise>6) career, including the basis for release from the service with reference to the section, subsection and clause of the applicable Act; </inglise>
<eesti>7) puhkused; </eesti>
<inglise>7) holidays; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ergutused, sealhulgas andmed riiklike teenetem&auml;rkide andmise kohta </eesti>
<inglise>8) incentives, including information concerning the grant of honorary decorations; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.12.96 j&otilde;ust.01.03.97 - RT I 1997, 1, 4) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.12.96 entered into force 01.03.97 - RT I 1997, 1, 4) </inglise>
<eesti>9) distsiplinaarkaristused ja nende kustutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>9) disciplinary punishments and their cancellation; </inglise>
<eesti>10) atesteerimistulemused. </eesti>
<inglise>10) evaluation results. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistuslehe vorm ja pidamise kord kehtestatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The form of and procedure for maintaining a service record shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 158. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 158. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistusleht teisele teenistuskohale asumisel v&otilde;i teenistusest vabastamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Service record upon transfer to another position or release from office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikule, kes lahkub teenistusest v&otilde;i reservist, antakse tema soovil teenistuslehe &auml;rakiri. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who resigns from the service or reserve shall be given a copy of the service record at his or her request. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametniku asumisel teisele teenistuskohale muus ametiasutuses saadetakse teenistusleht uude teenistuskohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the transfer of an official to another position in another administrative agency, his or her service record shall be sent to the new place of service. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistusest vabastamisel saadetakse teenistusleht Riigikantseleile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon release from the service, the service record shall be sent to the State Chancellery. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 159. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 159. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;raamat </eesti>
<inglise>Employment record book of official </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&otilde;hikohaga ametniku kohta peetakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahvis 20 s&auml;testatud korras t&ouml;&ouml;raamatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A employment record book shall be maintained pursuant to procedure provided for in &sect; 20 of the Employment Contracts Act with respect to an official who is on the regular staff. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse kantakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment record book shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametniku ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name and surname of the official; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ametniku s&uuml;nniaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date of birth of the official; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teenistuses oldud aeg, sealhulgas erikandega teenistuse aeg, mis annab &otilde;iguse sooduspensionile v&otilde;i pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i soodustatud korras arvutamisele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the period of employment in the service, including a service period by a special entry which entitles the official to a pension with benefits or to a preferential calculation of the years of pensionable service; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teenistussuhte peatumine k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 108 punkti 1 v&otilde;i 6 alusel kauemaks kui kolmeks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) suspension of the service relationship pursuant to clause 108 1) or 6) of this Act for longer than three months. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametniku n&otilde;udel kantakse t&ouml;&ouml;raamatusse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On the demand of an official, the employment record book shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teenistusest vabastamise aluse formuleering viitega seaduse paragrahvile, l&otilde;ikele ja punktile; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the basis for release from the service with reference to the section, subsection and clause of the applicable Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) andmed t&auml;idetud ametikohtade kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) information concerning positions filled; </inglise>
<eesti>3) (Kehtetu - 24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </eesti>
<inglise>3) (Repealed - 24.01.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </inglise>
<eesti>13. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 13 </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Settlement of Disputes </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 160. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 160. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste kohtulik lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Settlement of disputes in court </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikul on halduskohtumenetluse seadustiku (RT I 1993, 50, 694; 1994, 16, 290; 28, 425) paragrahv 7 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud &uuml;hekuulise t&auml;htaja jooksul &otilde;igus esitada kaebusi halduskohtule teenistusalastes k&uuml;simustes antud k&auml;skkirjade, korralduste ja otsuste ning sooritatud toimingute peale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official has the right to file a complaint with an administrative court against directives, orders and resolutions issued and acts performed concerning service-related issues, within a period of one month as provided for in subsection 7 (1) of the Code of Administrative Court Procedure (RT I 1993, 50, 694; 1994, 16, 290; 28, 425). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Abiteenistujal on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda t&ouml;&ouml;lepingust tulenevate vaidluste lahendamiseks maa- v&otilde;i linnakohtusse Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669) &sect; 143 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who is a member of support staff has the right of recourse to a county or city court for the settlement of disputes relating to an employment contract within a period provided for in &sect; 143 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669). </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.2000 entered into force 27.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 7, 18) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametnik v&otilde;ib halduskohtus n&otilde;uda k&auml;skkirja, korralduse, otsuse v&otilde;i toimingu t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt seadusevastaseks tunnistamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official may demand that a directive, order, resolution or act be declared unlawful in whole or in part by an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui kohus tunnistab ametniku teenistusest vabastamise v&otilde;i &uuml;leviimise kohta antud k&auml;skkirja, korralduse v&otilde;i otsuse seadusevastaseks, kuulub ametnik viivitamatult ennistamisele, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui ametnik loobub ennistamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a court declares a directive, order or resolution issued with respect to the release from the service or transfer of an official unlawful, the official shall be promptly reinstated, except if the official waives reinstatement. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ametnik v&otilde;ib kohtult taotleda temale m&auml;&auml;ratud distsiplinaarkaristuse t&uuml;histamist, kui ta leiab, et teda on karistatud ebaseaduslikult, sealhulgas s&uuml;&uuml;teo raskusele ja selle toimepanemise asjaoludele ilmselt mittevastava karistusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An official may request the cancellation by a court of a disciplinary punishment imposed on him or her if the official finds that he or she has been punished unlawfully, including a punishment which apparently does not correspond to the gravity of the offence and to the circumstances of its commission. </inglise>
<eesti>14. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 14 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 161. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 161. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti- v&otilde;i abiteenistuskoha muutmise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of change of position or support staff position </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise t&otilde;ttu muudetakse ametniku v&otilde;i abiteenistuja ameti- v&otilde;i abiteenistuskoha nimetust v&otilde;i v&auml;hendatakse palgam&auml;&auml;ra, teatatakse sellest teenistujale kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu enne muudatuse rakendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If due to the entry into force of this Act, the title of the position or support staff position of an official is changed, or the salary rate is reduced, a public servant shall be notified thereof in writing at least one month before implementation of the change. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ameti- v&otilde;i abiteenistuskoha nimetuse muutmisega mitten&otilde;ustumisel, kui muudatusega kaasneb palga v&auml;henemine v&otilde;i seni tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; laadi v&otilde;i keerukusastme muutumine, on teenistujal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda teenistusest vabastamist, teatades sellest kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon refusal to consent to a change of the title of the position or support staff position which brings about the reduction of salary or in a change of the nature or complexity of the current job, a public servant has the right to demand release from the service, giving at least two weeks' written notice thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike alusel teenistusest vabastatud isikule makstakse h&uuml;vitusena tema kahe kuu keskmine palk. </eesti>
<inglise>A person released from the service pursuant to this subsection shall be paid his or her two months' average salary as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ameti- v&otilde;i abiteenistuskoha nimetus, mida ei muudeta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel, j&auml;&auml;b j&otilde;usse ka p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist ja seda nimetust saab muuta ainult uute ametikohtade nimetuste kehtestamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The title of a position or support staff position determined by an employment contract, which is not changed pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, shall remain in force also after entry into force of this Act, and this title may only be changed by the establishment of new titles of position. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 162. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 162. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkursi korras t&auml;idetaval ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tava ametniku teenistussuhte j&auml;tkumine v&otilde;i l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Continuation or termination of service relationship of official employed in position filled by way of competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avaliku konkursita teenistusse v&otilde;etud ametnik, kelle ametikoht k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise t&otilde;ttu muutub konkursi korras t&auml;idetavaks, v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada niisugusel ametikohal kuni k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 178 s&auml;testatud ajal toimuva atesteerimiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who is employed in the service without public competition and whose position shall be filled by way of competition due to the entry into force of this Act may work in such position until his or her evaluation at the time provided for in &sect; 178 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ametnik tunnistatakse atesteerimisel ametikohale vastavaks, v&otilde;rdsustatakse atesteerimistulemused konkursitulemustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If, upon evaluation, an official specified in subsection (1) of this section is determined to be suitable for his or her position, evaluation results shall be equal to competition results. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ametnik tunnistatakse atesteerimisel ametikohale mittevastavaks, vabastatakse ta teenistusest k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 117 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 2 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, upon evaluation, an official specified in subsection (1) of this section is determined to be unsuitable for his or her position, the official shall be released from the service pursuant to clause 117 (1) 2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhul kuulutatakse ametikoha t&auml;itmiseks v&auml;lja avalik konkurss. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case provided for in subsection (3) of this section, a public competition to fill the vacant position shall be announced. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 163. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 163. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;etud ametniku teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &uuml;mbervormistamine v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;suhte l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Re-registration of employment in service or termination of employment relationship of official employed under employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kahe kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest, vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse alusel t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;etud ametnik nimetamise alusel teenistusse v&otilde;etuks tagasiulatuvalt, alates seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) During two months after the date of entry into force of this Act, an official employed pursuant to the Employment Contracts Act shall be registered as employed in the service by appointment, retroactively, as of the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;suhe ametnikuga, kes on t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;etud m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel ametikohale, mis k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 21 2. l&otilde;ike alusel eeldab m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks teenistusse v&otilde;tmist, vormistatakse poolte kokkuleppel m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks teenistusse v&otilde;tmiseks nelja kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest, v&otilde;i l&otilde;petatakse vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahv 86 punktile 3 t&ouml;&ouml;taja koondamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The employment relationship with an official who is employed under an employment contract for an unspecified period of time in a position which requires employment in the service for a specified period of time pursuant to subsection 21 (2) of this Act shall be registered, with the agreement of the parties, as employment in the service for a specified period of time within four months after the entry into force of this Act, or shall be terminated due to the lay-off of the official pursuant to clause 86 3) of the Employment Contracts Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 162 2. l&otilde;ike v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. v&otilde;i 2. l&otilde;ike alusel vormistatakse ametnik teenistusse v&otilde;etuks nimetamise alusel, annab ta k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 28 s&auml;testatud ametivande. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an official is registered as employed in the service by appointment pursuant to subsection 162 (2) of this Act or subsection (1) or (2) of this section, the official shall take the oath of office provided for in &sect; 28 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 164. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 164. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse alusel vabastatavad ametnikud </eesti>
<inglise>Officials released pursuant to Employment Contracts Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik, kes on enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist teatanud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest ette t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seadusega s&auml;testatud korras, vabastatakse teenistusest t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who, before entry into force of this Act, has given advance notice of the termination of his or her contract of employment pursuant to procedure provided for in the Employment Contracts Act shall be released from the service pursuant to the Employment Contracts Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik, kellele enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist teatati t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest ette t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seadusega s&auml;testatud korras, vabastatakse teenistusest t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official who, before entry into force of this Act, is given advance notice of the termination of his or her employment contract pursuant to procedure provided for in the Employment Contracts Act shall be released from the service pursuant to the Employment Contracts Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 165. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 165. </inglise>
<eesti>Varasema distsiplinaarkaristuse kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of earlier disciplinary punishment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkaristus, mis m&auml;&auml;rati enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist, on j&otilde;us ka p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary punishment imposed before entry into force of this Act shall also remain in force after entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Niisugune karistus t&auml;idetakse ja see kustub selle seaduse j&auml;rgi, mille alusel karistus m&auml;&auml;rati. </eesti>
<inglise>Such punishment shall be served and it shall expire pursuant to the Act on the basis of which the punishment was imposed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametnik v&otilde;ib enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist m&auml;&auml;ratud distsiplinaarkaristuse vaidlustada halduskohtus k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 160 alusel, kui selle karistuse suhtes puudub j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official may contest a disciplinary punishment imposed before entry into force of this Act in an administrative court pursuant to &sect; 160 of this Act if a court judgment regarding this punishment has not entered into force. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 166. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 166. </inglise>
<eesti>Varasema distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Imposition of punishment for earlier disciplinary offence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikule v&otilde;ib enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist toimepandud distsiplinaars&uuml;&uuml;teo eest m&auml;&auml;rata k&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud distsiplinaarkaristuse, kui talle ei ole selle s&uuml;&uuml;teo eest veel distsiplinaarkaristust m&auml;&auml;ratud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary punishment prescribed in this Act may be imposed on an official for a disciplinary offence committed before entry into force of this Act if no disciplinary punishment for that offence has yet been imposed on him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist toimepandud s&uuml;&uuml;teo eest ei v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rata madalamale palgaastmele &uuml;leviimist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall not be transferred to a lower salary grade for an offence committed before entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 167. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 167. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks teenistusse v&otilde;etud ametniku teenistuse l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of service of official employed in service for specified period of time </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistussuhe ametnikuga, kes enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist oli teenistusse v&otilde;etud m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks, l&otilde;peb teenistusse v&otilde;tmisel kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja saabumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>The service relationship with an official employed in the service for a specified period of time before entry into force of this Act shall terminate upon expiry of the term determined upon employment. </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistussuhte j&auml;tkumisel p&auml;rast nimetatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist m&auml;&auml;ratakse uus t&auml;htaeg v&otilde;i vormistatakse ametnik teenistusse v&otilde;etuks m&auml;&auml;ramata ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the service relationship continues after expiry of such term, a new term shall be specified, or the official shall be registered as employed in the service for an unspecified period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 168. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 168. </inglise>
<eesti>Erand vanuse ja hariduse n&otilde;udest </eesti>
<inglise>Exception to age and education requirement </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvides 14 ja 15 ametniku vanuse ja hariduse suhtes kehtestatud n&otilde;uded ei laiene ametnikule, kes on teenistuses k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements regarding the age and education of an official established in &sect;&sect; 14 and 15 of this Act shall not extend to an official who is in the service at the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 169. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 169. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lismaalase teenistussuhte l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of service relationship of alien </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnikud, kes k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;eval ei ole Eesti kodakondsuses, vabastatakse teenistusest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi alusel hiljemalt 1997. aasta 1. veebruaril. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State officials who are not citizens of Estonia at the date of entry into force of this Act shall be released from the service pursuant to this section not later than 1 February 1997. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.12.95 entered into force 01.01.96 - RT I 1995, 97, 1664) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuametis, Politseiametis ja P&auml;&auml;steametis lubatakse kolme aasta jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest arvates ametnikuna t&ouml;&ouml;tada isikutel, kes taotlevad Eesti kodakondsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons who apply for Estonian citizenship shall be permitted to work as officials at the Tax Board, the Police Administration and the Rescue Board during three years after entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vanglates lubatakse 2004. aasta 1. jaanuarini edasi t&ouml;&ouml;tada teenistuses olevatel: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following persons who are employed in prisons may continue their service until 1 January 2004: </inglise>
<eesti>1) nooremametnikel ning I ja II klassi valvuritel, kellel on 2001. aasta 1. jaanuari seisuga kehtiv elamisluba Eestis elamiseks ja kes ei ole m&otilde;ne muu riigi kodakondsuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) junior officials and class 1 and 2 guards who, as at 1 January 2001, hold valid residence permits for residing in Estonia and are not citizens of another state; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vanemametnikel ning I ja II klassi vanglainspektoritel, kes 2001. aasta 1. jaanuariks on esitanud sooviavalduse Eesti kodakondsuse saamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) senior officials and class 1 and 2 prison inspectors who have submitted requests for acquisition of Estonian citizenship by 1 January 2001; </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&otilde;rgematel ametnikel ja vangla peainspektoritel, kes 2001. aasta 1. jaanuariks on esitanud sooviavalduse Eesti kodakondsuse saamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) higher officials and chief prison inspectors who have submitted requests for acquisition of Estonian citizenship by 1 January 2001. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 672) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 672) </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (1)) Vanglates t&ouml;&ouml;tavad ametnikud, kes ei ole Eesti kodakondsuses ja kes ei vasta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes esitatud tingimustele, vabastatakse teenistusest hiljemalt 2001. aasta 1. m&auml;rtsil. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (1)) Officials employed in prisons who do not hold Estonian citizenship and who do not meet the requirements set in subsection (3) of this section shall be released from service not later than 1 March 2001. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 672) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 672) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel vabastatud isikule makstakse h&uuml;vitusena tema &uuml;he kuu ametipalk. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person released from the service pursuant to subsection (1) of this section shall be paid his or her one month's salary as compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 170. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 170. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;tamise l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of employment with another employer </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, kelle &uuml;le ta teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise korras teostab j&auml;relevalvet, on kohustatud &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, l&otilde;petama t&ouml;&ouml;vahekorra teise t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga v&otilde;i lahkuma teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>An official working for another employer over whom the official exercises supervision in performing his or her duties is required to terminate the employment relationship with the employer or resign from the service within one month after the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 171. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 171. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;tamisest teatamine ja sellise t&ouml;&ouml;tamise lubamise otsustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of employment with another employer and decision on permission of such employment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuja, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, keda ei ole nimetatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 170, on kohustatud teatama sellest oma vahetule &uuml;lemusele &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public servant working for another employer who is not specified in &sect; 170 of this Act is required to notify his or her immediate superior thereof within one week after the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahetu &uuml;lemus, kelle alluv t&ouml;&ouml;tab teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, on kohustatud &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud teate saamise p&auml;evast, otsustama, kas niisugune t&ouml;&ouml;tamine on lubatav. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An immediate superior whose subordinate works for another employer is required to decide whether such employment is permissible, within one month after the date of receipt of the notice specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohakaasluse lubamisel peab vahetu &uuml;lemus sama t&auml;htaja jooksul otsustama, missuguse koormusega ja missugusel ajal v&otilde;ib teenistuja t&ouml;&ouml;tada teise t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures. </eesti>
<inglise>If double employment is permitted, the immediate superior must decide, within the same period, the work load and time the public servant may work for the other employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohakaasluse keelamise v&otilde;i piiramise korral on teenistuja kohustatud &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates talle keelu v&otilde;i piirangu teatavakstegemise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evast, l&otilde;petama kohakaasluse v&otilde;i esitama teisele t&ouml;&ouml;andjale avalduse lubatud ajal ja koormusega t&ouml;&ouml;tamise kohta v&otilde;i lahkuma teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>If double employment is prohibited or restricted, the public servant shall be required, within one month after the working day following notification of the prohibition or restriction, to terminate double employment, submit to the other employer an application for employment at the time and with the work load permitted or resign from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 172. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 172. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatamine tulundus&uuml;hendusse kuulumisest </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of membership in commercial association </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik, kes on tulundus&uuml;henduse liige, on kohustatud teatama sellest oma vahetule &uuml;lemusele &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>An official who is a member of a commercial association is required to notify his or her immediate superior thereof within one week after the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 173. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 173. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatamine ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelemisest </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of engagement in enterprise </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnik, kes tegeleb ettev&otilde;tlusega, on kohustatud teatama sellest &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state official who is engaged in enterprise is required to notify a person or administrative agency authorised to employ him or her thereof within one week after the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus, peab &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud teate saamise p&auml;evast, otsustama, kas ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelemine on &uuml;hitatav teenistusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person or administrative agency with employment authority shall decide within one month after the date of receipt of the notice specified in subsection (1) of this section whether engagement in enterprise may be combined with the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hitamise keelamisel peab ametnik kuue kuu jooksul, arvates talle keelu teatavakstegemise p&auml;evast, l&otilde;petama ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelemise v&otilde;i lahkuma teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>If such combination is prohibited, an official shall, within six months after the date of being notified of the prohibition, terminate his or her engagement in enterprise or resign from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 174. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 174. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hendusest ja erakonnast lahkumise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to resign from union or political party </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiametnik, kes teostab teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise korras j&auml;relevalvet &uuml;henduse v&otilde;i erakonna tegevuse &uuml;le, mille liikmeks ta on, peab teatama oma liikmelisusest &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus, ja lahkuma &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, niisugusest &uuml;hendusest v&otilde;i erakonnast v&otilde;i teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>A state official who, in performing his or her duties, exercises supervision over an association or political party of which he or she is a member shall notify a person or administrative agency authorised to employ him or her of his or her membership within one week after the date of entry into force of this Act and, within one month after the date of entry into force of this Act, shall resign from such association or political party, or from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 175. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 175. </inglise>
<eesti>Tulundus&uuml;henduse ja erakonna organitest lahkumise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to resign from bodies of commercial association or political party </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiametnik, kes kuulub tulundus&uuml;henduse v&otilde;i erakonna alaliselt tegutsevasse juht-, kontroll- v&otilde;i revisjoniorganisse, v&auml;lja arvatud riigi osalusega ettev&otilde;tte juhtimis- v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorganisse, on kohustatud teatama sellest &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus, ja lahkuma &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, tulundus&uuml;henduse v&otilde;i erakonna organist v&otilde;i teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>A state official who belongs to the permanent directing, control or audit body of a commercial association or political party, except the directing or supervisory body of an enterprise with state participation, is required to notify a person or administrative agency authorised to employ him or her thereof within one week after the date of entry into force of this Act and, within one month after the date of entry into force of this Act, to resign from the body of the commercial association or party, or from the service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 176. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 176. </inglise>
<eesti>Relvi valdavasse organisatsiooni kuuluva ametniku kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of official belonging to organisation which possesses weapons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiametnik, samuti riigiametiasutuse abiteenistuja, kes kuulub relvi valdavasse, s&otilde;jav&auml;eliselt korraldatud v&otilde;i s&otilde;jalisi harjutusi harrastavasse organisatsiooni, on kohustatud teatama oma liikmelisusest &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast, isikule v&otilde;i ametiasutusele, kellel on tema teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state official or a member of the support staff of a state administrative agency who belongs to an organisation which possesses weapons, is militarily organised or performs military exercises is required to notify a person or administrative agency authorised to employ him or her of the membership within one week after the date of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik v&otilde;i ametiasutus, kellel on teenistusse v&otilde;tmise &otilde;igus, peab &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud teate saamise p&auml;evast, otsustama, kas teenistuja v&otilde;ib kuuluda sellesse organisatsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person or administrative agency with employment authority shall decide, within one month after the date of receipt of the notice specified in subsection (1) of this section, whether a public servant may belong to such organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikesse organisatsioonidesse, jahimeeste &uuml;hendustesse ning &uuml;ldteadaolevatesse ja -tunnustatud spordiorganisatsioonidesse kuulumist ei v&otilde;i keelata. </eesti>
<inglise>Membership in state organisations, hunters' associations, and generally known and recognised sports organisations shall not be prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistuja, kelle kuulumine organisatsiooni keelati k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike alusel, on kohustatud &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates talle keelu teatavakstegemise p&auml;evast, lahkuma nimetatud organisatsioonist v&otilde;i teenistusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A public servant whose membership in an organisation is prohibited pursuant to subsection (2) of this section is required to resign, within one month after the date of being notified of the prohibition, from such organisation or the service. </inglise>
